{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781761432636,"sessionID":"ses_126bf8e50ffelsFwMkoTKm6SCe","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_9hweezBn1Z1akigT8xhgZdIk","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/review-r2/lineages/gpt55r2-b-2","offset":1,"limit":200},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/review-r2/lineages/gpt55r2-b-2</path>\n<type>directory</type>\n<entries>\n.executor-state/\n\n(1 entries)\n</entries>","metadata":{"preview":".executor-state/","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"directory","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/review-r2/lineages/gpt55r2-b-2","entries":[".executor-state/"],"offset":1,"totalEntries":1,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/review-r2/lineages/gpt55r2-b-2","time":{"start":1781761432631,"end":1781761432636}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0e0048a0bc91479b016a33859888ac819181a48c2e1ad0114c"}},"id":"prt_ed941dc0e001NgiqQahjW5UA4U","sessionID":"ses_126bf8e50ffelsFwMkoTKm6SCe","messageID":"msg_ed941ad890011407BiJHC7Vm9R"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781761432699,"sessionID":"ses_126bf8e50ffelsFwMkoTKm6SCe","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_8C6SmalDzFM58LzBmAksVQmM","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/review-r2/scopes/B-rest-of-002/spec.md","offset":1,"limit":400},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/review-r2/scopes/B-rest-of-002/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Audit Scope — Memory Store / Index / Lifecycle (002 non-search)\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Independent gpt-5.5 deep-review **audit** of the memory store, index, and write-lifecycle code of the system-spec-kit MCP server — the 002-memory-store-and-search surface OUTSIDE the search/retrieval pipeline and outside the 017-021 fixes. REVIEW-SCOPE target (no new implementation). Report real P0/P1/P2 findings with `file:line` evidence; clean PASS is valid.\n5: \n6: ## Code under review\n7: All paths under `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/`:\n8: - `handlers/memory-index.ts` and the write/index/scan handlers — memory write safety, index scan, causal write lifecycle\n9: - `lib/storage/` — maintenance markers, storage/index maintenance, retention\n10: - `lib/ops/` — job-store, batch-processor, scan-job orchestration, cancellation lifecycle\n11: - semantic trigger fallback, learning-feedback reducers, memclaw-derived memory hardening, OpenLTM retrieval/observability + continuity/resilience, provenance injection, idempotency flag-on correctness (the 002 store/index modules under `handlers/` and `lib/`)\n12: \n13: ## Review dimensions\n14: correctness, security (SQL/injection, path handling), data integrity (write safety, idempotency, causal lifecycle), concurrency/cancellation, performance, maintainability, spec-vs-code drift. Emphasize write-path safety, transaction boundaries, and cancellation/cleanup correctness.\n15: \n16: ## Notes\n17: This round BROADENS beyond 017-021. Focus on store/index/lifecycle code, not the search/retrieval pipeline (covered by scope A).\n\n(End of file - total 17 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Audit Scope — Memory Store / Index / Lifecycle (002 non-search)\n\n## Purpose\nIndependent gpt-5.5 deep-review **audit** of the memory store, index, and write-lifecycle code of the system-spec-kit MCP server — the 002-memory-store-and-search surface OUTSIDE the search/retrieval pipeline and outside the 017-021 fixes. REVIEW-SCOPE target (no new implementation). Report real P0/P1/P2 findings with `file:line` evidence; clean PASS is valid.\n\n## Code under review\nAll paths under `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/`:\n- `handlers/memory-index.ts` and the write/index/scan handlers — memory write safety, index scan, causal write lifecycle\n- `lib/storage/` — maintenance markers, storage/index maintenance, retention\n- `lib/ops/` — job-store, batch-processor, scan-job orchestration, cancellation lifecycle\n- semantic trigger fallback, learning-feedback reducers, memclaw-derived memory hardening, OpenLTM retrieval/observability + continuity/resilience, provenance injection, idempotency flag-on correctness (the 002 store/index modules under `handlers/` and `lib/`)\n\n## Review dimensions\ncorrectness, security (SQL/injection, path handling), data integrity (write safety, idempotency, causal lifecycle), concurrency/cancellation, performance, maintainability, spec-vs-code drift. Emphasize write-path safety, transaction boundaries, and cancellation/cleanup correctness.\n\n## Notes\nThis round BROADENS beyond 017-021. Focus on store/index/lifecycle code, not the search/retrieval pipeline (covered by scope A).","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/review-r2/scopes/B-rest-of-002/spec.md","text":"# Audit Scope — Memory Store / Index / Lifecycle (002 non-search)\n\n## Purpose\nIndependent gpt-5.5 deep-review **audit** of the memory store, index, and write-lifecycle code of the system-spec-kit MCP server — the 002-memory-store-and-search surface OUTSIDE the search/retrieval pipeline and outside the 017-021 fixes. REVIEW-SCOPE target (no new implementation). Report real P0/P1/P2 findings with `file:line` evidence; clean PASS is valid.\n\n## Code under review\nAll paths under `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/`:\n- `handlers/memory-index.ts` and the write/index/scan handlers — memory write safety, index scan, causal write lifecycle\n- `lib/storage/` — maintenance markers, storage/index maintenance, retention\n- `lib/ops/` — job-store, batch-processor, scan-job orchestration, cancellation lifecycle\n- semantic trigger fallback, learning-feedback reducers, memclaw-derived memory hardening, OpenLTM retrieval/observability + continuity/resilience, provenance injection, idempotency flag-on correctness (the 002 store/index modules under `handlers/` and `lib/`)\n\n## Review dimensions\ncorrectness, security (SQL/injection, path handling), data integrity (write safety, idempotency, causal lifecycle), concurrency/cancellation, performance, maintainability, spec-vs-code drift. Emphasize write-path safety, transaction boundaries, and cancellation/cleanup correctness.\n\n## Notes\nThis round BROADENS beyond 017-021. Focus on store/index/lifecycle code, not the search/retrieval pipeline (covered by scope A).","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":17,"totalLines":17,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/review-r2/scopes/B-rest-of-002/spec.md","time":{"start":1781761432694,"end":1781761432698}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0e0048a0bc91479b016a33859888c48191ab4d013407a9277a"}},"id":"prt_ed941dc5000147Ic6CW39dTt2S","sessionID":"ses_126bf8e50ffelsFwMkoTKm6SCe","messageID":"msg_ed941ad890011407BiJHC7Vm9R"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781761432713,"sessionID":"ses_126bf8e50ffelsFwMkoTKm6SCe","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_pHcxQs3bjKnuZA8v0g6s66y6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","offset":261,"limit":360},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n261:         classify:\n262:           fresh: \"None of the three state artifacts exist\"\n263:           resume: \"Config, JSONL, and strategy all exist and config.mode == 'review' and agree on target/spec folder\"\n264:           completed-session: \"Resume artifacts exist and config.status == 'complete'\"\n265:           invalid-state: \"Any partial, missing, or contradictory combination\"\n266:         outputs:\n267:           - session_state: \"fresh | resume | completed-session | invalid-state\"\n268:         on_resume:\n269:           log: \"Auto-resume: state artifacts are complete and consistent. Continue the same lineage (sessionId unchanged, generation unchanged, no archive).\"\n270:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":{iteration_count},\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":null,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n271:           skip_to: phase_loop\n272:         on_restart:\n273:           action: \"Archive the current review packet under the root-level review_archive/ tree and start a new lineage segment with a fresh sessionId and generation+1.\"\n274:           command: \"if [ -d {state_paths.packet_dir} ]; then mkdir -p {state_paths.archive_root} && mv {state_paths.packet_dir} {state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}; fi\"\n275:           set:\n276:             lineage_mode: \"restart\"\n277:             parent_session_id: \"{prior_session_id}\"\n278:             generation: \"{prior_generation + 1}\"\n279:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"restarted\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{prior_session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"restart\",\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":\"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n280:           skip_to: step_create_config\n281:         note_deferred_branches: \"fork and completed-continue are deferred and no longer runtime-supported in this release. The reducer still reads `lineageMode` from config for dashboards and analysis, but only `new`, `resume`, and `restart` are live. See deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branches for the one-session contract.\"\n282:         on_completed_session:\n283:           log: \"Prior session already completed. Either archive the completed review/ tree and start a fresh session, or jump straight to synthesis with the existing artifacts.\"\n284:           skip_to: phase_synthesis\n285:         on_invalid_state:\n286:           halt: true\n287:           message: \"Existing deep-review state in review/ is incomplete or contradictory. Repair or archive the invalid review packet before continuing.\"\n288:         on_fresh:\n289:           action: \"Proceed with a new session\"\n290: \n291:       step_scope_discovery:\n292:         action: \"Resolve review target to a concrete file list based on target type\"\n293:         resolve:\n294:           spec-folder: |\n295:             1. Read spec.md, plan.md, tasks.md, checklist.md, implementation-summary.md\n296:             2. Discover implementation files referenced in spec artifacts\n297:             3. Discover test files associated with implementation\n298:             4. Set scope = all discovered files\n299:           skill: |\n300:             1. Read SKILL.md from .opencode/skills/{skill_name}/\n301:             2. Discover references/, assets/, scripts/ contents\n302:             3. Find agent definitions referencing this skill across runtimes\n303:             4. Find command entry points referencing this skill\n304:             5. Set scope = all discovered files\n305:           agent: |\n306:             1. Find agent definition across repo-managed runtimes (.claude/agents/, .opencode/agents/, .codex/agents/, .agents/)\n307:             2. Compare agent definitions for consistency\n308:             3. Set scope = all discovered agent files\n309:           track: |\n310:             1. List all child spec folders under specs/{track}/ or .opencode/specs/{track}/\n311:             2. For each: read spec.md + checklist.md\n312:             3. Set scope = all child spec artifacts\n313:           files: |\n314:             1. Expand glob patterns from review_target\n315:             2. Validate all files exist\n316:             3. Discover immediate cross-references (imports, links)\n317:             4. Set scope = expanded file list + cross-references\n318:         outputs:\n319:           - review_scope_files: \"List of all files in review scope\"\n320:           - cross_reference_targets: \"{ spec_paths: [...], code_paths: [...], test_paths: [...] }\"\n321: \n322:       step_order_dimensions:\n323:         action: \"Order review dimensions based on risk priority\"\n324:         algorithm: |\n325:           1. Iteration 0 (inventory pass): Build artifact map, identify file types, estimate complexity\n326:           2. Subsequent iterations follow risk-ordered deep passes:\n327:              correctness → security → traceability → maintainability\n328:           3. If review_dimensions != \"all\", filter to only requested dimensions\n329:           4. Derive traceability protocol plan:\n330:              - core: spec_code, checklist_evidence\n331:              - overlay: skill_agent, agent_cross_runtime, feature_catalog_code, playbook_capability\n332:           5. If resource_map_present, reserve at least one traceability-oriented pass to cross-check target_files from applied/T-*.md against resource-map.md and classify touched / expected-by-scope / gap / absent-from-map outcomes\n333:           6. Store ordered list as dimension_queue\n334:         outputs:\n335:           - dimension_queue: \"Ordered list of dimensions to review\"\n336:           - inventory_pass: true\n337: \n338:       step_normalize_review_dimensions:\n339:         action: \"Normalize reviewDimensions once during init for config + JSONL reuse\"\n340:         outputs:\n341:           - review_dimensions_normalized: \"Canonical string[] for deep-review-config.json\"\n342:           - review_dimensions_json: \"JSON.stringify(review_dimensions_normalized) for JSONL config record\"\n343:         normalize: |\n344:           Accept {review_dimensions} in any of these shapes and convert once:\n345:             - \"all\" → [\"correctness\",\"security\",\"traceability\",\"maintainability\"]\n346:             - \"correctness,security\" → [\"correctness\",\"security\"]\n347:             - [\"correctness\"] → [\"correctness\"]\n348:           Every element MUST be one of the four canonical dimension names.\n349: \n350:       step_create_config:\n351:         action: \"Create deep-review-config.json from template with review-specific fields\"\n352:         template: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_config.json\n353:         populate:\n354:           topic: \"Review: {review_target}\"\n355:           mode: \"review\"\n356:           sessionId: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n357:           parentSessionId: null\n358:           lineageMode: \"new\"\n359:           generation: 1\n360:           continuedFromRun: null\n361:           reviewTarget: \"{review_target}\"\n362:           reviewTargetType: \"{review_target_type}\"\n363:           # Reuse the single normalized init-time value from step_normalize_review_dimensions.\n364:           reviewDimensions: \"{review_dimensions_normalized}\"\n365:           resource_map_present: \"{resource_map_present}\"\n366:           reviewScopeFiles: \"{review_scope_files}\"\n367:           severityThreshold: \"P2\"\n368:           crossReference:\n369:             core: [\"spec_code\", \"checklist_evidence\"]\n370:             overlay: [\"skill_agent\", \"agent_cross_runtime\", \"feature_catalog_code\", \"playbook_capability\"]\n371:           maxIterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n372:           # Semantic: weighted P0/P1/P2 severity ratio. See SKILL.md §\"Convergence Threshold Semantics\".\n373:           convergenceThreshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n374:           stuckThreshold: 2\n375:           maxDurationMinutes: 120\n376:           specFolder: \"{spec_folder}\"\n377:           # <!-- F-010-B5-04 -->\n378:           # Honor the parsed --no-resource-map flag from deep-review.md:71 (default true; false when flag is set).\n379:           # The markdown command parses $ARGUMENTS and binds {resource_map_emit} before this step runs.\n380:           resource_map.emit: \"{resource_map_emit}\"\n381:           createdAt: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n382:           status: \"initialized\"\n383:           releaseReadinessState: \"in-progress\"\n384:           executionMode: \"auto\"\n385:         output: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n386: \n387:       step_create_state_log:\n388:         action: \"Initialize JSONL state log with config record including review fields and lineage metadata\"\n389:         note: \"Reuse review_dimensions_json from step_normalize_review_dimensions. Never re-normalize or wrap the raw template value.\"\n390:         # <!-- F-010-B5-04 -->\n391:         # Same parsed --no-resource-map flag honored here so config and state_log agree from line 1.\n392:         content: '{\"type\":\"config\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"reviewTarget\":\"{review_target}\",\"reviewTargetType\":\"{review_target_type}\",\"reviewDimensions\":{review_dimensions_json},\"resource_map_present\":{resource_map_present},\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":{resource_map_emit}},\"sessionId\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"parentSessionId\":null,\"lineageMode\":\"new\",\"generation\":1,\"continuedFromRun\":null,\"maxIterations\":{max_iterations},\"convergenceThreshold\":{convergence_threshold},\"createdAt\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"specFolder\":\"{spec_folder}\"}'\n393:         output: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n394: \n395:       step_create_findings_registry:\n396:         action: \"Initialize reducer-owned review findings registry\"\n397:         content: '{\"sessionId\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"generation\":1,\"lineageMode\":\"new\",\"openFindings\":[],\"resolvedFindings\":[],\"repeatedFindings\":[],\"dimensionCoverage\":{\"correctness\":false,\"security\":false,\"traceability\":false,\"maintainability\":false},\"findingsBySeverity\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":0,\"P2\":0},\"openFindingsCount\":0,\"resolvedFindingsCount\":0,\"convergenceScore\":0.0}'\n398:         output: \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n399: \n400:       step_create_strategy:\n401:         action: \"Create review strategy file from deep_review_strategy.md template\"\n402:         template: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_strategy.md\n403:         populate:\n404:           review_target: \"{review_target}\"\n405:           review_target_type: \"{review_target_type}\"\n406:           dimensions: \"{dimension_queue}\"\n407:           scope_files: \"{review_scope_files}\"\n408:           cross_reference_targets: \"{cross_reference_targets}\"\n409:           max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n410:           convergence_threshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n411:         output: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n412: \n413:       step_enrich_strategy_context:\n414:         action: \"Ensure Known Context is written only after strategy.md exists\"\n415:         condition: \"prior_context_found\"\n416:         edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n417:         note: \"Append or replace the Known Context section with prior_context_summary and retained detail from prior_context\"\n418: \n419:       step_enrich_strategy_resource_map:\n420:         action: \"Inject resource-map status into Known Context after strategy.md exists\"\n421:         edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n422:         note: \"When resource_map_present is true, append the resource_map_known_context snapshot and add Resource Map Coverage to the Review Charter. When false, append 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n423: \n424:       step_init_complete:\n425:         log: \"Initialization complete. Config, state, and strategy files created. Review scope: {review_scope_files_count} files, {dimension_queue_count} dimensions.\"\n426:         set: { current_iteration: 1, stuck_count: 0, p0_count: 0, p1_count: 0, p2_count: 0 }\n427: \n428:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n429:   # PHASE 2: ITERATION LOOP\n430:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n431:   phase_loop:\n432:     purpose: Dispatch review agent iterations until convergence\n433:     repeat: true\n434:     max_repeats: \"{max_iterations}\"\n435:     steps:\n436: \n437:       step_read_state:\n438:         action: \"Read current state from JSONL, strategy, and config\"\n439:         read:\n440:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n441:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n442:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n443:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n444:         extract:\n445:           - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n446:           - current_iteration: \"iteration_count + 1\"\n447:           - last_newFindingsRatio: \"Extract newFindingsRatio from last iteration record\"\n448:           - last_focus: \"Extract focus/dimension from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n449:           - ratio_prev: \"Extract newFindingsRatio from second-latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n450:           - ratio_latest: \"Extract newFindingsRatio from latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n451:           - next_dimension: \"Next uncovered dimension from dimension_queue in strategy.md\"\n452:           - dimensions_covered: \"List of dimensions already reviewed\"\n453:           - dimensions_remaining: \"List of dimensions not yet reviewed\"\n454:           - dimension_coverage: \"covered / total dimensions\"\n455:           - coverage_age: \"Iterations since dimension coverage last changed; require >= 1 before STOP\"\n456:           - p0_count: \"Count P0 findings across all iterations\"\n457:           - p1_count: \"Count P1 findings across all iterations\"\n458:           - p2_count: \"Count P2 findings across all iterations\"\n459:           - resource_map_present: \"Extract boolean from deep-review-config.json, default false\"\n460:           - resource_map_prompt_line: \"If resource_map_present is true, return 'Resource Map Coverage: cross-check target_files from {spec_folder}/applied/T-*.md against {spec_folder}/resource-map.md and classify only missed coverage as gaps.' Else return 'Resource Map Coverage: resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate.'\"\n461:           - session_id: \"Extract sessionId from deep-review-config.json\"\n462:           - generation: \"Extract generation from deep-review-config.json, else 1\"\n463:           - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records as 'run N: dimension (ratio, P0/P1/P2)'\"\n464:           - latest_status: \"Extract status from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n465:           - last_claim_adjudication_passed: \"Scan state.jsonl for the most recent `claim_adjudication` event; use its `passed` boolean. Default true when no event exists or when activeP0 + activeP1 == 0 (gate is vacuous without adjudicable findings).\"\n466:           - claim_adjudication_active_count: \"Count of active P0/P1 findings at the time of the last claim_adjudication event; 0 when none exist\"\n467:           - security_sensitive_fix_scope: \"Boolean true when the current review is a rerun after fixes involving security, path disclosure, auth/authz, sandboxing, env precedence, public schemas, persistence, or user-visible error payloads; derive from the latest review report, remediation notes, or planning packet when present, else false.\"\n468:           - fix_completeness_replay_required_rows: \"Count prior active or remediated P0/P1 findings, plus any prior security/path P2 findings, that require closed-gate replay before STOP.\"\n469:           - fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows: \"Count required replay rows marked PASS with file:line or command evidence and producer/consumer/matrix coverage.\"\n470: \n471:       step_check_pause_sentinel:\n472:         action: \"Check for pause sentinel file\"\n473:         check: \"Does {state_paths.pause_sentinel} exist?\"\n474:         if_exists:\n475:           set:\n476:             pending_stop_event: \"paused\"\n477:             pending_stop_reason: \"userPaused\"\n478:             pending_stop_detail: \"sentinel file detected\"\n479:           skip_to: step_normalize_pause_events\n480:         if_not_exists:\n481:           proceed: true\n482: \n483:       step_graph_convergence:\n484:         action: \"Evaluate coverage-graph convergence before the inline review convergence vote\"\n485:         inspect:\n486:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n487:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n488:         transform: |\n489:           1. Call graph convergence on the current review lineage before the inline 3-signal vote.\n490:           2. Record the decision as one of CONTINUE, STOP_ALLOWED, STOP_BLOCKED.\n491:           3. Preserve raw graph signals and blockers for reducer rollup and blocked-stop evidence.\n492:           4. Normalize blockers to both JSON array and CSV forms for downstream stop handling.\n493:           5. Set graph_stop_blocked = true only when graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\".\n494:         bash: 'node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs --spec-folder \"{spec_folder}\" --loop-type \"review\" --session-id \"{session_id}\"'\n495:         note: \"Invoke the runtime script directly. Review-side graph convergence must run before the inline review stop vote.\"\n496:         append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"graph_convergence\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"decision\":\"{graph_decision}\",\"signals\":{graph_signals_json},\"blockers\":{graph_blockers_json},\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n497:         outputs:\n498:           - graph_decision: \"CONTINUE | STOP_ALLOWED | STOP_BLOCKED\"\n499:           - graph_signals_json: \"JSON object returned by convergence.cjs\"\n500:           - graph_blockers_json: \"JSON array of graph blockers when present, else []\"\n501:           - graph_blockers_csv: \"Comma-separated blocker summary when graph blocks STOP, else empty string\"\n502:           - graph_stop_blocked: \"Boolean true when graph_decision == STOP_BLOCKED\"\n503: \n504:       step_check_convergence:\n505:         action: \"Evaluate graph-assisted review stop conditions and the legal-stop decision tree\"\n506:         algorithm: |\n507:           0. CLAIM-ADJUDICATION PRE-CHECK (universal STOP veto; runs before hard stops and composite convergence):\n508:              claim_adjudication_gate_pass = (last_claim_adjudication_passed != false) OR (p0_count + p1_count == 0)\n509:              If claim_adjudication_gate_pass == false:\n510:                candidate_decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n511:                stop_blocked = true\n512:                stopReason = \"blockedStop\"\n513:                blocked_gates = [\"claimAdjudicationGate\"]\n514:                recovery_strategy = \"Reviewer must add typed claim-adjudication packets (claim, evidenceRefs, counterevidenceSought, alternativeExplanation, finalSeverity, confidence, downgradeTrigger) for every active P0/P1 finding before STOP is allowed.\"\n515:                Skip hard stops (1) and composite convergence (4); proceed directly to step 5 legal-stop decision-tree assembly so blocked_by_json, gate outputs, and the blocked_stop event still populate consistently.\n516:           1. HARD STOPS:\n517:              a) if iteration_count >= max_iterations: set decision = \"STOP\", stopReason = \"maxIterationsReached\", hard_stop_reason = \"max_iterations_reached\", preserve any failed legal-stop gates as terminal evidence, and proceed to synthesis without legal-stop veto\n518:              b) if all dimensions clean AND required traceability protocols are covered AND p0_count == 0 AND p1_count == 0 AND coverage_age >= 1 AND all quality gates pass (evidence: every P0/P1 has file:line; scope: all findings within target; coverage: all dimensions reviewed): mark hard_stop_reason = \"all_dimensions_clean\" and promote to STOP candidate\n519:              Operator stop reasons (`maxIterationsReached`, `manualStop`, `userPaused`, unrecoverable `error`) are terminal ceilings. They do not hide failed gates; they record them in synthesis and stop dispatch.\n520:           2. STUCK DETECTION (threshold 2):\n521:              if stuck_count >= 2: STUCK_RECOVERY\n522:           3. GRAPH CONVERGENCE PREREQUISITE:\n523:                graph_decision, graph_signals_json, and graph_blockers_json are already populated by step_graph_convergence.\n524:                Final STOP is never legal unless the inline review vote says STOP AND graph_decision == \"STOP_ALLOWED\".\n525:                If graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\", set stop_blocked = true and route through blocked_stop emission instead of stopping.\n526:           4. COMPOSITE CONVERGENCE (3-signal weighted vote with split thresholds):\n527:                signals = []\n528:                a) Rolling average (w=0.30, window=2, needs 2+ iterations):\n529:                   avg = mean(last 2 newFindingsRatios)\n530:                   stop if avg <= 0.08\n531:                b) MAD noise floor (w=0.25, needs 3+ iterations):\n532:                   noiseFloor = MAD(all ratios) * 1.4826\n533:                   stop if latest ratio <= noiseFloor\n534:                c) Dimension coverage (w=0.45):\n535:                   coverage = dimensions_covered / total_dimensions\n536:                   stop if coverage >= 1.0 AND required traceability protocols are covered AND coverage_age >= 1\n537:                Redistribute weights for unavailable signals.\n538:                if latest ratio <= 0.05: mark no_progress_threshold_reached\n539:                if weighted_stop_score >= 0.60: inline STOP becomes a candidate and binary gates must run\n540:           5. LEGAL-STOP DECISION TREE (review-specific gates; runs whenever step 0, all-dimensions-clean, or the composite vote promotes STOP to a candidate; terminal max-iteration/manual/error stops bypass veto and record failed gates as evidence):\n541:                a) convergenceGate: pass when a hard-stop condition is met OR weighted_stop_score >= 0.60; record score\n542:                b) dimensionCoverageGate: pass when configured dimensions and required traceability coverage are complete and coverage_age >= 1; record covered and missing dimensions\n543:                c) p0ResolutionGate: pass when activeP0 == 0; record activeP0\n544:                d) evidenceDensityGate: pass when every active P0/P1 has concrete file:line evidence and no active P0/P1 relies only on inference; record avgEvidencePerFinding\n545:                e) hotspotSaturationGate: pass when review hotspots have been revisited enough times to satisfy the saturation heuristic\n546:                f) claimAdjudicationGate: pass when claim_adjudication_gate_pass == true (i.e. last_claim_adjudication_passed != false OR there are no active P0/P1 findings to adjudicate); record last_claim_adjudication_passed and claim_adjudication_active_count\n547:                g) fixCompletenessReplayGate: pass when security_sensitive_fix_scope == false OR every required closed-gate replay row passes with file:line or command evidence and producer/consumer/matrix coverage; record security_sensitive_fix_scope, fix_completeness_replay_required_rows, and fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows\n548:                h) candidateCoverageGate: skip entirely when `reviewDepthSchemaVersion` is not 2 on the latest iteration. Otherwise pass when the current iteration's `reviewDepthApplicability.scopeClass` is `trivial` with `enforcement: \"skip\"` AND `reviewDepthApplicability.evidenceRefs` is non-empty, OR when the reducer registry's `searchDebt` is empty AND `candidateCoverage.covered` is a superset of `searchCoverage.requiredBugClasses` for the lineage. Otherwise pass = false; record `searchDebt` items as blocked-stop evidence; blocker name = \"candidateCoverageGate\"; recovery_strategy = \"Resolve deferred/blocked obligations in next iteration or downgrade scope explicitly to trivial with cited evidence.\"\n549:                i) graphlessFallbackGate: skip when `reviewDepthSchemaVersion` is not 2 OR the reducer registry's last-iteration `searchCoverage.graphCoverageMode` is `graph`. Applies when graphCoverageMode is `graphless_fallback` or `unavailable_blocked`. Pass when graphCoverageMode is `graphless_fallback` AND at least one `searchLedger` row exists for each entry in `searchCoverage.requiredBugClasses` with `searchActions[].method` in {\"direct_read\",\"exact_grep\",\"semantic_search\",\"code_graph_status_check\",\"producer_consumer_trace\",\"negative_test_inspection\"} AND non-empty `evidenceRefs`. Fail automatically when graphCoverageMode is `unavailable_blocked`; record the explicit unavailability reason. Otherwise pass = false; blocker name = \"graphlessFallbackGate\"; recovery_strategy = \"Add cited fallback ledger rows (direct read, exact search, producer/consumer trace, negative-test inspection) or set graphCoverageMode to 'graph' once graph data is available.\"\n550:              if STOP is a candidate and any gate fails:\n551:                decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n552:                stop_blocked = true\n553:                stopReason = \"blockedStop\"\n554:                blocked_by_json = JSON array of failing gate names (always include \"claimAdjudicationGate\" when claim_adjudication_gate_pass == false, \"fixCompletenessReplayGate\" when fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass == false, \"candidateCoverageGate\" when candidate_coverage_gate_pass == false, and \"graphlessFallbackGate\" when graphless_fallback_gate_pass == false)\n555:                blocked_by_csv = comma-separated list of failing gate names\n556:                convergence_gate_pass = boolean\n557:                convergence_gate_score = numeric convergence score\n558:                dimension_coverage_gate_pass = boolean\n559:                dimension_coverage_gate_covered_json = JSON array of covered review dimensions\n560:                dimension_coverage_gate_missing_json = JSON array of missing review dimensions\n561:                p0_resolution_gate_pass = boolean\n562:                active_p0_count = number of active P0 findings\n563:                evidence_density_gate_pass = boolean\n564:                avg_evidence_per_finding = numeric evidence density\n565:                hotspot_saturation_gate_pass = boolean\n566:                claim_adjudication_gate_pass = boolean\n567:                claim_adjudication_active_count = numeric count of active P0/P1 at the gate\n568:                fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass = boolean\n569:                security_sensitive_fix_scope = boolean\n570:                fix_completeness_replay_required_rows = numeric count of closed-gate replay rows required for security-sensitive fix reruns\n571:                fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows = numeric count of required closed-gate replay rows marked PASS with evidence\n572:                candidate_coverage_gate_pass = boolean\n573:                candidate_coverage_search_debt_json = JSON array of reducer-owned searchDebt obligations blocking STOP, else []\n574:                candidate_coverage_missing_json = JSON array of required bug classes not present in candidateCoverage.covered, else []\n575:                graphless_fallback_gate_pass = boolean\n576:                graphless_fallback_mode = latest reducer-owned searchCoverage.graphCoverageMode value\n577:                graphless_fallback_missing_json = JSON array of required bug classes without cited fallback ledger rows, else []\n578:                graphless_fallback_unavailability_reason = explicit reason when graphCoverageMode == \"unavailable_blocked\", else empty string\n579:                recovery_strategy = one-line hint describing the next review action needed to satisfy the failed gates; combine candidateCoverageGate and graphlessFallbackGate recovery guidance when both fail (when claimAdjudicationGate is the failing gate, prefer the step-0 recovery_strategy already set)\n580:           6. COMBINED STOP RULE:\n581:                a) if STOP is legal AND graph_decision == \"STOP_ALLOWED\": decision = \"STOP\"\n582:                b) if STOP is legal AND graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\":\n583:                     decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n584:                     stop_blocked = true\n585:                     stopReason = \"blockedStop\"\n586:                     # Blocked-stop closure: blockedBy must be string[] per the\n587:                     # published review blocked-stop contract. Extract the `.type`\n588:                     # field from each structured graph blocker; preserve the full\n589:                     # objects in graph_blocker_detail_json for operator inspection.\n590:                     blocked_by_json = JSON.stringify(graph_blockers_json.map(b => typeof b === \"string\" ? b : (b && b.type) || \"graph_blocker\"))\n591:                     blocked_by_csv = graph_blockers_csv\n592:                     graph_blocker_detail_json = graph_blockers_json\n593:                     recovery_strategy = \"Resolve review coverage-graph blockers before stopping.\"\n594:                c) if STOP is legal AND graph_decision == \"CONTINUE\":\n595:                     decision = \"CONTINUE\"\n596:                     stop_blocked = false\n597:                     reason = \"graph_convergence_continue\"\n598:                d) else keep the existing STUCK_RECOVERY or CONTINUE outcome\n599:         outputs:\n600:           - decision: \"STOP | BLOCKED | STUCK_RECOVERY | CONTINUE\"\n601:           - reason: \"Human-readable stop reason\"\n602:           - stop_blocked: \"Boolean true when STOP is vetoed by inline legal-stop gates or graph_decision == STOP_BLOCKED\"\n603:           - blocked_by_json: \"JSON array of failed legal-stop gates when decision == BLOCKED\"\n604:           - blocked_by_csv: \"Comma-separated list of failed legal-stop gates when decision == BLOCKED\"\n605:           - convergence_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for convergenceGate\"\n606:           - convergence_gate_score: \"Numeric score recorded for convergenceGate\"\n607:           - dimension_coverage_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for dimensionCoverageGate\"\n608:           - dimension_coverage_gate_covered_json: \"JSON array of covered review dimensions\"\n609:           - dimension_coverage_gate_missing_json: \"JSON array of missing review dimensions\"\n610:           - p0_resolution_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for p0ResolutionGate\"\n611:           - active_p0_count: \"Active P0 finding count at stop-check time\"\n612:           - evidence_density_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for evidenceDensityGate\"\n613:           - avg_evidence_per_finding: \"Numeric evidence density for active findings\"\n614:           - hotspot_saturation_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for hotspotSaturationGate\"\n615:           - claim_adjudication_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for claimAdjudicationGate (false vetoes STOP)\"\n616:           - claim_adjudication_active_count: \"Count of active P0/P1 findings evaluated by claimAdjudicationGate\"\n617:           - fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for fixCompletenessReplayGate (false vetoes STOP on security-sensitive fix reruns)\"\n618:           - security_sensitive_fix_scope: \"Boolean true when the review is a security-sensitive fix rerun\"\n619:           - fix_completeness_replay_required_rows: \"Count of closed-gate replay rows required before STOP\"\n620:           - fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows: \"Count of required closed-gate replay rows that passed with evidence\"\n\n(Showing lines 261-620 of 1441. Use offset=621 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"        classify:\n          fresh: \"None of the three state artifacts exist\"\n          resume: \"Config, JSONL, and strategy all exist and config.mode == 'review' and agree on target/spec folder\"\n          completed-session: \"Resume artifacts exist and config.status == 'complete'\"\n          invalid-state: \"Any partial, missing, or contradictory combination\"\n        outputs:\n          - session_state: \"fresh | resume | completed-session | invalid-state\"\n        on_resume:\n          log: \"Auto-resume: state artifacts are complete and consistent. Continue the same lineage (sessionId unchanged, generation unchanged, no archive).\"\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":{iteration_count},\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":null,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          skip_to: phase_loop\n        on_restart:\n          action: \"Archive the current review packet under the root-level review_archive/ tree and start a new lineage segment with a fresh sessionId and generation+1.\"\n          command: \"if [ -d {state_paths.packet_dir} ]; then mkdir -p {state_paths.archive_root} && mv {state_paths.packet_dir} {state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}; fi\"\n          set:\n            lineage_mode: \"restart\"\n            parent_session_id: \"{prior_session_id}\"\n            generation: \"{prior_generation + 1}\"\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"restarted\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{prior_session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"restart\",\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":\"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          skip_to: step_create_config","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","text":"        classify:\n          fresh: \"None of the three state artifacts exist\"\n          resume: \"Config, JSONL, and strategy all exist and config.mode == 'review' and agree on target/spec folder\"\n          completed-session: \"Resume artifacts exist and config.status == 'complete'\"\n          invalid-state: \"Any partial, missing, or contradictory combination\"\n        outputs:\n          - session_state: \"fresh | resume | completed-session | invalid-state\"\n        on_resume:\n          log: \"Auto-resume: state artifacts are complete and consistent. Continue the same lineage (sessionId unchanged, generation unchanged, no archive).\"\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":{iteration_count},\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":null,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          skip_to: phase_loop\n        on_restart:\n          action: \"Archive the current review packet under the root-level review_archive/ tree and start a new lineage segment with a fresh sessionId and generation+1.\"\n          command: \"if [ -d {state_paths.packet_dir} ]; then mkdir -p {state_paths.archive_root} && mv {state_paths.packet_dir} {state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}; fi\"\n          set:\n            lineage_mode: \"restart\"\n            parent_session_id: \"{prior_session_id}\"\n            generation: \"{prior_generation + 1}\"\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"restarted\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{prior_session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"restart\",\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":\"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          skip_to: step_create_config\n        note_deferred_branches: \"fork and completed-continue are deferred and no longer runtime-supported in this release. The reducer still reads `lineageMode` from config for dashboards and analysis, but only `new`, `resume`, and `restart` are live. See deep-review/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branches for the one-session contract.\"\n        on_completed_session:\n          log: \"Prior session already completed. Either archive the completed review/ tree and start a fresh session, or jump straight to synthesis with the existing artifacts.\"\n          skip_to: phase_synthesis\n        on_invalid_state:\n          halt: true\n          message: \"Existing deep-review state in review/ is incomplete or contradictory. Repair or archive the invalid review packet before continuing.\"\n        on_fresh:\n          action: \"Proceed with a new session\"\n\n      step_scope_discovery:\n        action: \"Resolve review target to a concrete file list based on target type\"\n        resolve:\n          spec-folder: |\n            1. Read spec.md, plan.md, tasks.md, checklist.md, implementation-summary.md\n            2. Discover implementation files referenced in spec artifacts\n            3. Discover test files associated with implementation\n            4. Set scope = all discovered files\n          skill: |\n            1. Read SKILL.md from .opencode/skills/{skill_name}/\n            2. Discover references/, assets/, scripts/ contents\n            3. Find agent definitions referencing this skill across runtimes\n            4. Find command entry points referencing this skill\n            5. Set scope = all discovered files\n          agent: |\n            1. Find agent definition across repo-managed runtimes (.claude/agents/, .opencode/agents/, .codex/agents/, .agents/)\n            2. Compare agent definitions for consistency\n            3. Set scope = all discovered agent files\n          track: |\n            1. List all child spec folders under specs/{track}/ or .opencode/specs/{track}/\n            2. For each: read spec.md + checklist.md\n            3. Set scope = all child spec artifacts\n          files: |\n            1. Expand glob patterns from review_target\n            2. Validate all files exist\n            3. Discover immediate cross-references (imports, links)\n            4. Set scope = expanded file list + cross-references\n        outputs:\n          - review_scope_files: \"List of all files in review scope\"\n          - cross_reference_targets: \"{ spec_paths: [...], code_paths: [...], test_paths: [...] }\"\n\n      step_order_dimensions:\n        action: \"Order review dimensions based on risk priority\"\n        algorithm: |\n          1. Iteration 0 (inventory pass): Build artifact map, identify file types, estimate complexity\n          2. Subsequent iterations follow risk-ordered deep passes:\n             correctness → security → traceability → maintainability\n          3. If review_dimensions != \"all\", filter to only requested dimensions\n          4. Derive traceability protocol plan:\n             - core: spec_code, checklist_evidence\n             - overlay: skill_agent, agent_cross_runtime, feature_catalog_code, playbook_capability\n          5. If resource_map_present, reserve at least one traceability-oriented pass to cross-check target_files from applied/T-*.md against resource-map.md and classify touched / expected-by-scope / gap / absent-from-map outcomes\n          6. Store ordered list as dimension_queue\n        outputs:\n          - dimension_queue: \"Ordered list of dimensions to review\"\n          - inventory_pass: true\n\n      step_normalize_review_dimensions:\n        action: \"Normalize reviewDimensions once during init for config + JSONL reuse\"\n        outputs:\n          - review_dimensions_normalized: \"Canonical string[] for deep-review-config.json\"\n          - review_dimensions_json: \"JSON.stringify(review_dimensions_normalized) for JSONL config record\"\n        normalize: |\n          Accept {review_dimensions} in any of these shapes and convert once:\n            - \"all\" → [\"correctness\",\"security\",\"traceability\",\"maintainability\"]\n            - \"correctness,security\" → [\"correctness\",\"security\"]\n            - [\"correctness\"] → [\"correctness\"]\n          Every element MUST be one of the four canonical dimension names.\n\n      step_create_config:\n        action: \"Create deep-review-config.json from template with review-specific fields\"\n        template: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_config.json\n        populate:\n          topic: \"Review: {review_target}\"\n          mode: \"review\"\n          sessionId: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n          parentSessionId: null\n          lineageMode: \"new\"\n          generation: 1\n          continuedFromRun: null\n          reviewTarget: \"{review_target}\"\n          reviewTargetType: \"{review_target_type}\"\n          # Reuse the single normalized init-time value from step_normalize_review_dimensions.\n          reviewDimensions: \"{review_dimensions_normalized}\"\n          resource_map_present: \"{resource_map_present}\"\n          reviewScopeFiles: \"{review_scope_files}\"\n          severityThreshold: \"P2\"\n          crossReference:\n            core: [\"spec_code\", \"checklist_evidence\"]\n            overlay: [\"skill_agent\", \"agent_cross_runtime\", \"feature_catalog_code\", \"playbook_capability\"]\n          maxIterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n          # Semantic: weighted P0/P1/P2 severity ratio. See SKILL.md §\"Convergence Threshold Semantics\".\n          convergenceThreshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n          stuckThreshold: 2\n          maxDurationMinutes: 120\n          specFolder: \"{spec_folder}\"\n          # <!-- F-010-B5-04 -->\n          # Honor the parsed --no-resource-map flag from deep-review.md:71 (default true; false when flag is set).\n          # The markdown command parses $ARGUMENTS and binds {resource_map_emit} before this step runs.\n          resource_map.emit: \"{resource_map_emit}\"\n          createdAt: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n          status: \"initialized\"\n          releaseReadinessState: \"in-progress\"\n          executionMode: \"auto\"\n        output: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n\n      step_create_state_log:\n        action: \"Initialize JSONL state log with config record including review fields and lineage metadata\"\n        note: \"Reuse review_dimensions_json from step_normalize_review_dimensions. Never re-normalize or wrap the raw template value.\"\n        # <!-- F-010-B5-04 -->\n        # Same parsed --no-resource-map flag honored here so config and state_log agree from line 1.\n        content: '{\"type\":\"config\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"reviewTarget\":\"{review_target}\",\"reviewTargetType\":\"{review_target_type}\",\"reviewDimensions\":{review_dimensions_json},\"resource_map_present\":{resource_map_present},\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":{resource_map_emit}},\"sessionId\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"parentSessionId\":null,\"lineageMode\":\"new\",\"generation\":1,\"continuedFromRun\":null,\"maxIterations\":{max_iterations},\"convergenceThreshold\":{convergence_threshold},\"createdAt\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"specFolder\":\"{spec_folder}\"}'\n        output: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n\n      step_create_findings_registry:\n        action: \"Initialize reducer-owned review findings registry\"\n        content: '{\"sessionId\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"generation\":1,\"lineageMode\":\"new\",\"openFindings\":[],\"resolvedFindings\":[],\"repeatedFindings\":[],\"dimensionCoverage\":{\"correctness\":false,\"security\":false,\"traceability\":false,\"maintainability\":false},\"findingsBySeverity\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":0,\"P2\":0},\"openFindingsCount\":0,\"resolvedFindingsCount\":0,\"convergenceScore\":0.0}'\n        output: \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n\n      step_create_strategy:\n        action: \"Create review strategy file from deep_review_strategy.md template\"\n        template: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/deep_review_strategy.md\n        populate:\n          review_target: \"{review_target}\"\n          review_target_type: \"{review_target_type}\"\n          dimensions: \"{dimension_queue}\"\n          scope_files: \"{review_scope_files}\"\n          cross_reference_targets: \"{cross_reference_targets}\"\n          max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n          convergence_threshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n        output: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n\n      step_enrich_strategy_context:\n        action: \"Ensure Known Context is written only after strategy.md exists\"\n        condition: \"prior_context_found\"\n        edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        note: \"Append or replace the Known Context section with prior_context_summary and retained detail from prior_context\"\n\n      step_enrich_strategy_resource_map:\n        action: \"Inject resource-map status into Known Context after strategy.md exists\"\n        edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        note: \"When resource_map_present is true, append the resource_map_known_context snapshot and add Resource Map Coverage to the Review Charter. When false, append 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n\n      step_init_complete:\n        log: \"Initialization complete. Config, state, and strategy files created. Review scope: {review_scope_files_count} files, {dimension_queue_count} dimensions.\"\n        set: { current_iteration: 1, stuck_count: 0, p0_count: 0, p1_count: 0, p2_count: 0 }\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 2: ITERATION LOOP\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_loop:\n    purpose: Dispatch review agent iterations until convergence\n    repeat: true\n    max_repeats: \"{max_iterations}\"\n    steps:\n\n      step_read_state:\n        action: \"Read current state from JSONL, strategy, and config\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n        extract:\n          - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n          - current_iteration: \"iteration_count + 1\"\n          - last_newFindingsRatio: \"Extract newFindingsRatio from last iteration record\"\n          - last_focus: \"Extract focus/dimension from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n          - ratio_prev: \"Extract newFindingsRatio from second-latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n          - ratio_latest: \"Extract newFindingsRatio from latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n          - next_dimension: \"Next uncovered dimension from dimension_queue in strategy.md\"\n          - dimensions_covered: \"List of dimensions already reviewed\"\n          - dimensions_remaining: \"List of dimensions not yet reviewed\"\n          - dimension_coverage: \"covered / total dimensions\"\n          - coverage_age: \"Iterations since dimension coverage last changed; require >= 1 before STOP\"\n          - p0_count: \"Count P0 findings across all iterations\"\n          - p1_count: \"Count P1 findings across all iterations\"\n          - p2_count: \"Count P2 findings across all iterations\"\n          - resource_map_present: \"Extract boolean from deep-review-config.json, default false\"\n          - resource_map_prompt_line: \"If resource_map_present is true, return 'Resource Map Coverage: cross-check target_files from {spec_folder}/applied/T-*.md against {spec_folder}/resource-map.md and classify only missed coverage as gaps.' Else return 'Resource Map Coverage: resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate.'\"\n          - session_id: \"Extract sessionId from deep-review-config.json\"\n          - generation: \"Extract generation from deep-review-config.json, else 1\"\n          - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records as 'run N: dimension (ratio, P0/P1/P2)'\"\n          - latest_status: \"Extract status from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n          - last_claim_adjudication_passed: \"Scan state.jsonl for the most recent `claim_adjudication` event; use its `passed` boolean. Default true when no event exists or when activeP0 + activeP1 == 0 (gate is vacuous without adjudicable findings).\"\n          - claim_adjudication_active_count: \"Count of active P0/P1 findings at the time of the last claim_adjudication event; 0 when none exist\"\n          - security_sensitive_fix_scope: \"Boolean true when the current review is a rerun after fixes involving security, path disclosure, auth/authz, sandboxing, env precedence, public schemas, persistence, or user-visible error payloads; derive from the latest review report, remediation notes, or planning packet when present, else false.\"\n          - fix_completeness_replay_required_rows: \"Count prior active or remediated P0/P1 findings, plus any prior security/path P2 findings, that require closed-gate replay before STOP.\"\n          - fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows: \"Count required replay rows marked PASS with file:line or command evidence and producer/consumer/matrix coverage.\"\n\n      step_check_pause_sentinel:\n        action: \"Check for pause sentinel file\"\n        check: \"Does {state_paths.pause_sentinel} exist?\"\n        if_exists:\n          set:\n            pending_stop_event: \"paused\"\n            pending_stop_reason: \"userPaused\"\n            pending_stop_detail: \"sentinel file detected\"\n          skip_to: step_normalize_pause_events\n        if_not_exists:\n          proceed: true\n\n      step_graph_convergence:\n        action: \"Evaluate coverage-graph convergence before the inline review convergence vote\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n        transform: |\n          1. Call graph convergence on the current review lineage before the inline 3-signal vote.\n          2. Record the decision as one of CONTINUE, STOP_ALLOWED, STOP_BLOCKED.\n          3. Preserve raw graph signals and blockers for reducer rollup and blocked-stop evidence.\n          4. Normalize blockers to both JSON array and CSV forms for downstream stop handling.\n          5. Set graph_stop_blocked = true only when graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\".\n        bash: 'node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs --spec-folder \"{spec_folder}\" --loop-type \"review\" --session-id \"{session_id}\"'\n        note: \"Invoke the runtime script directly. Review-side graph convergence must run before the inline review stop vote.\"\n        append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"graph_convergence\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"decision\":\"{graph_decision}\",\"signals\":{graph_signals_json},\"blockers\":{graph_blockers_json},\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}'\n        outputs:\n          - graph_decision: \"CONTINUE | STOP_ALLOWED | STOP_BLOCKED\"\n          - graph_signals_json: \"JSON object returned by convergence.cjs\"\n          - graph_blockers_json: \"JSON array of graph blockers when present, else []\"\n          - graph_blockers_csv: \"Comma-separated blocker summary when graph blocks STOP, else empty string\"\n          - graph_stop_blocked: \"Boolean true when graph_decision == STOP_BLOCKED\"\n\n      step_check_convergence:\n        action: \"Evaluate graph-assisted review stop conditions and the legal-stop decision tree\"\n        algorithm: |\n          0. CLAIM-ADJUDICATION PRE-CHECK (universal STOP veto; runs before hard stops and composite convergence):\n             claim_adjudication_gate_pass = (last_claim_adjudication_passed != false) OR (p0_count + p1_count == 0)\n             If claim_adjudication_gate_pass == false:\n               candidate_decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n               stop_blocked = true\n               stopReason = \"blockedStop\"\n               blocked_gates = [\"claimAdjudicationGate\"]\n               recovery_strategy = \"Reviewer must add typed claim-adjudication packets (claim, evidenceRefs, counterevidenceSought, alternativeExplanation, finalSeverity, confidence, downgradeTrigger) for every active P0/P1 finding before STOP is allowed.\"\n               Skip hard stops (1) and composite convergence (4); proceed directly to step 5 legal-stop decision-tree assembly so blocked_by_json, gate outputs, and the blocked_stop event still populate consistently.\n          1. HARD STOPS:\n             a) if iteration_count >= max_iterations: set decision = \"STOP\", stopReason = \"maxIterationsReached\", hard_stop_reason = \"max_iterations_reached\", preserve any failed legal-stop gates as terminal evidence, and proceed to synthesis without legal-stop veto\n             b) if all dimensions clean AND required traceability protocols are covered AND p0_count == 0 AND p1_count == 0 AND coverage_age >= 1 AND all quality gates pass (evidence: every P0/P1 has file:line; scope: all findings within target; coverage: all dimensions reviewed): mark hard_stop_reason = \"all_dimensions_clean\" and promote to STOP candidate\n             Operator stop reasons (`maxIterationsReached`, `manualStop`, `userPaused`, unrecoverable `error`) are terminal ceilings. They do not hide failed gates; they record them in synthesis and stop dispatch.\n          2. STUCK DETECTION (threshold 2):\n             if stuck_count >= 2: STUCK_RECOVERY\n          3. GRAPH CONVERGENCE PREREQUISITE:\n               graph_decision, graph_signals_json, and graph_blockers_json are already populated by step_graph_convergence.\n               Final STOP is never legal unless the inline review vote says STOP AND graph_decision == \"STOP_ALLOWED\".\n               If graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\", set stop_blocked = true and route through blocked_stop emission instead of stopping.\n          4. COMPOSITE CONVERGENCE (3-signal weighted vote with split thresholds):\n               signals = []\n               a) Rolling average (w=0.30, window=2, needs 2+ iterations):\n                  avg = mean(last 2 newFindingsRatios)\n                  stop if avg <= 0.08\n               b) MAD noise floor (w=0.25, needs 3+ iterations):\n                  noiseFloor = MAD(all ratios) * 1.4826\n                  stop if latest ratio <= noiseFloor\n               c) Dimension coverage (w=0.45):\n                  coverage = dimensions_covered / total_dimensions\n                  stop if coverage >= 1.0 AND required traceability protocols are covered AND coverage_age >= 1\n               Redistribute weights for unavailable signals.\n               if latest ratio <= 0.05: mark no_progress_threshold_reached\n               if weighted_stop_score >= 0.60: inline STOP becomes a candidate and binary gates must run\n          5. LEGAL-STOP DECISION TREE (review-specific gates; runs whenever step 0, all-dimensions-clean, or the composite vote promotes STOP to a candidate; terminal max-iteration/manual/error stops bypass veto and record failed gates as evidence):\n               a) convergenceGate: pass when a hard-stop condition is met OR weighted_stop_score >= 0.60; record score\n               b) dimensionCoverageGate: pass when configured dimensions and required traceability coverage are complete and coverage_age >= 1; record covered and missing dimensions\n               c) p0ResolutionGate: pass when activeP0 == 0; record activeP0\n               d) evidenceDensityGate: pass when every active P0/P1 has concrete file:line evidence and no active P0/P1 relies only on inference; record avgEvidencePerFinding\n               e) hotspotSaturationGate: pass when review hotspots have been revisited enough times to satisfy the saturation heuristic\n               f) claimAdjudicationGate: pass when claim_adjudication_gate_pass == true (i.e. last_claim_adjudication_passed != false OR there are no active P0/P1 findings to adjudicate); record last_claim_adjudication_passed and claim_adjudication_active_count\n               g) fixCompletenessReplayGate: pass when security_sensitive_fix_scope == false OR every required closed-gate replay row passes with file:line or command evidence and producer/consumer/matrix coverage; record security_sensitive_fix_scope, fix_completeness_replay_required_rows, and fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows\n               h) candidateCoverageGate: skip entirely when `reviewDepthSchemaVersion` is not 2 on the latest iteration. Otherwise pass when the current iteration's `reviewDepthApplicability.scopeClass` is `trivial` with `enforcement: \"skip\"` AND `reviewDepthApplicability.evidenceRefs` is non-empty, OR when the reducer registry's `searchDebt` is empty AND `candidateCoverage.covered` is a superset of `searchCoverage.requiredBugClasses` for the lineage. Otherwise pass = false; record `searchDebt` items as blocked-stop evidence; blocker name = \"candidateCoverageGate\"; recovery_strategy = \"Resolve deferred/blocked obligations in next iteration or downgrade scope explicitly to trivial with cited evidence.\"\n               i) graphlessFallbackGate: skip when `reviewDepthSchemaVersion` is not 2 OR the reducer registry's last-iteration `searchCoverage.graphCoverageMode` is `graph`. Applies when graphCoverageMode is `graphless_fallback` or `unavailable_blocked`. Pass when graphCoverageMode is `graphless_fallback` AND at least one `searchLedger` row exists for each entry in `searchCoverage.requiredBugClasses` with `searchActions[].method` in {\"direct_read\",\"exact_grep\",\"semantic_search\",\"code_graph_status_check\",\"producer_consumer_trace\",\"negative_test_inspection\"} AND non-empty `evidenceRefs`. Fail automatically when graphCoverageMode is `unavailable_blocked`; record the explicit unavailability reason. Otherwise pass = false; blocker name = \"graphlessFallbackGate\"; recovery_strategy = \"Add cited fallback ledger rows (direct read, exact search, producer/consumer trace, negative-test inspection) or set graphCoverageMode to 'graph' once graph data is available.\"\n             if STOP is a candidate and any gate fails:\n               decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n               stop_blocked = true\n               stopReason = \"blockedStop\"\n               blocked_by_json = JSON array of failing gate names (always include \"claimAdjudicationGate\" when claim_adjudication_gate_pass == false, \"fixCompletenessReplayGate\" when fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass == false, \"candidateCoverageGate\" when candidate_coverage_gate_pass == false, and \"graphlessFallbackGate\" when graphless_fallback_gate_pass == false)\n               blocked_by_csv = comma-separated list of failing gate names\n               convergence_gate_pass = boolean\n               convergence_gate_score = numeric convergence score\n               dimension_coverage_gate_pass = boolean\n               dimension_coverage_gate_covered_json = JSON array of covered review dimensions\n               dimension_coverage_gate_missing_json = JSON array of missing review dimensions\n               p0_resolution_gate_pass = boolean\n               active_p0_count = number of active P0 findings\n               evidence_density_gate_pass = boolean\n               avg_evidence_per_finding = numeric evidence density\n               hotspot_saturation_gate_pass = boolean\n               claim_adjudication_gate_pass = boolean\n               claim_adjudication_active_count = numeric count of active P0/P1 at the gate\n               fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass = boolean\n               security_sensitive_fix_scope = boolean\n               fix_completeness_replay_required_rows = numeric count of closed-gate replay rows required for security-sensitive fix reruns\n               fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows = numeric count of required closed-gate replay rows marked PASS with evidence\n               candidate_coverage_gate_pass = boolean\n               candidate_coverage_search_debt_json = JSON array of reducer-owned searchDebt obligations blocking STOP, else []\n               candidate_coverage_missing_json = JSON array of required bug classes not present in candidateCoverage.covered, else []\n               graphless_fallback_gate_pass = boolean\n               graphless_fallback_mode = latest reducer-owned searchCoverage.graphCoverageMode value\n               graphless_fallback_missing_json = JSON array of required bug classes without cited fallback ledger rows, else []\n               graphless_fallback_unavailability_reason = explicit reason when graphCoverageMode == \"unavailable_blocked\", else empty string\n               recovery_strategy = one-line hint describing the next review action needed to satisfy the failed gates; combine candidateCoverageGate and graphlessFallbackGate recovery guidance when both fail (when claimAdjudicationGate is the failing gate, prefer the step-0 recovery_strategy already set)\n          6. COMBINED STOP RULE:\n               a) if STOP is legal AND graph_decision == \"STOP_ALLOWED\": decision = \"STOP\"\n               b) if STOP is legal AND graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\":\n                    decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n                    stop_blocked = true\n                    stopReason = \"blockedStop\"\n                    # Blocked-stop closure: blockedBy must be string[] per the\n                    # published review blocked-stop contract. Extract the `.type`\n                    # field from each structured graph blocker; preserve the full\n                    # objects in graph_blocker_detail_json for operator inspection.\n                    blocked_by_json = JSON.stringify(graph_blockers_json.map(b => typeof b === \"string\" ? b : (b && b.type) || \"graph_blocker\"))\n                    blocked_by_csv = graph_blockers_csv\n                    graph_blocker_detail_json = graph_blockers_json\n                    recovery_strategy = \"Resolve review coverage-graph blockers before stopping.\"\n               c) if STOP is legal AND graph_decision == \"CONTINUE\":\n                    decision = \"CONTINUE\"\n                    stop_blocked = false\n                    reason = \"graph_convergence_continue\"\n               d) else keep the existing STUCK_RECOVERY or CONTINUE outcome\n        outputs:\n          - decision: \"STOP | BLOCKED | STUCK_RECOVERY | CONTINUE\"\n          - reason: \"Human-readable stop reason\"\n          - stop_blocked: \"Boolean true when STOP is vetoed by inline legal-stop gates or graph_decision == STOP_BLOCKED\"\n          - blocked_by_json: \"JSON array of failed legal-stop gates when decision == BLOCKED\"\n          - blocked_by_csv: \"Comma-separated list of failed legal-stop gates when decision == BLOCKED\"\n          - convergence_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for convergenceGate\"\n          - convergence_gate_score: \"Numeric score recorded for convergenceGate\"\n          - dimension_coverage_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for dimensionCoverageGate\"\n          - dimension_coverage_gate_covered_json: \"JSON array of covered review dimensions\"\n          - dimension_coverage_gate_missing_json: \"JSON array of missing review dimensions\"\n          - p0_resolution_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for p0ResolutionGate\"\n          - active_p0_count: \"Active P0 finding count at stop-check time\"\n          - evidence_density_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for evidenceDensityGate\"\n          - avg_evidence_per_finding: \"Numeric evidence density for active findings\"\n          - hotspot_saturation_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for hotspotSaturationGate\"\n          - claim_adjudication_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for claimAdjudicationGate (false vetoes STOP)\"\n          - claim_adjudication_active_count: \"Count of active P0/P1 findings evaluated by claimAdjudicationGate\"\n          - fix_completeness_replay_gate_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for fixCompletenessReplayGate (false vetoes STOP on security-sensitive fix reruns)\"\n          - security_sensitive_fix_scope: \"Boolean true when the review is a security-sensitive fix rerun\"\n          - fix_completeness_replay_required_rows: \"Count of closed-gate replay rows required before STOP\"\n          - fix_completeness_replay_passing_rows: \"Count of required closed-gate replay rows that passed with evidence\"","lineStart":261,"lineEnd":620,"totalLines":1441,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","time":{"start":1781761432705,"end":1781761432712}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0e0048a0bc91479b016a33859888d481919c3ea0bd5cebd4a4"}},"id":"prt_ed941dc79001djcEYTLDNV3YoV","sessionID":"ses_126bf8e50ffelsFwMkoTKm6SCe","messageID":"msg_ed941ad890011407BiJHC7Vm9R"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781761432747,"sessionID":"ses_126bf8e50ffelsFwMkoTKm6SCe","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_me5stxfJlMPjYiSSCnL0Pzdw","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_outputs.md","offset":1,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_outputs.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Deep Review State Outputs\"\n3: description: \"Focused reference for deep-review packet files, markdown outputs, reducer-owned views, and synthesis artifacts.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep review state outputs\"\n6:   - \"review packet outputs\"\n7:   - \"review dashboard output\"\n8:   - \"review report output\"\n9: importance_tier: normal\n10: contextType: implementation\n11: ---\n12: \n13: # Deep Review State Outputs\n14: \n15: This reference explains the files operators read during and after a review loop. Use `references/state/state_format.md` for schemas and field-level contracts.\n16: \n17: ---\n18: \n19: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n20: \n21: Deep-review outputs are audit artifacts. Iteration agents write evidence, the reducer writes derived state, and synthesis writes the release-readiness report.\n22: \n23: ---\n24: \n25: ## 2. PACKET FILES\n26: \n27: | File | Owner | Mutability | Purpose |\n28: |------|-------|------------|---------|\n29: | `deep-review-config.json` | Workflow | Immutable after init | Run parameters, lineage, threshold settings |\n30: | `deep-review-state.jsonl` | Workflow and iteration contract | Append-only | Config, iteration, blocked-stop, pause, synthesis events |\n31: | `deep-review-findings-registry.json` | Reducer | Regenerated | Active, resolved, repeated, and blocked findings |\n32: | `deep-review-strategy.md` | Reducer with operator-readable sections | Regenerated/updated | Dimension order, known context, next focus |\n33: | `deep-review-dashboard.md` | Reducer | Regenerated | Current status, trend, verdict preview |\n34: | `iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Iteration agent | Write-once | Detailed findings for one pass |\n35: | `review-report.md` | Synthesis | Final output | Findings-first release-readiness report |\n36: | `resource-map.md` | Synthesis | Final or disabled | Converged delta evidence map |\n37: \n38: ---\n39: \n40: ## 3. ITERATION MARKDOWN\n41: \n42: Each iteration file must be non-empty and end with exactly one final verdict line:\n43: \n44: ```text\n45: Review verdict: PASS\n46: ```\n47: \n48: ```text\n49: Review verdict: CONDITIONAL\n50: ```\n51: \n52: ```text\n53: Review verdict: FAIL\n54: ```\n55: \n56: The line maps to the findings in that iteration only. Synthesis computes the final release verdict from the full state.\n57: \n58: ---\n59: \n60: ## 4. DASHBOARD\n61: \n62: The dashboard is a status view, not the source of truth. It should display:\n63: \n64: - Current iteration and next focus.\n65: - Active P0/P1/P2 counts.\n66: - Dimension coverage.\n67: - Convergence trend.\n68: - Gate blockers.\n69: - Provisional verdict.\n70: \n71: If dashboard data disagrees with JSONL, JSONL wins and the reducer must regenerate the dashboard.\n72: \n73: ---\n74: \n75: ## 5. FINAL REPORT\n76: \n77: `review-report.md` is the handoff artifact. It carries:\n78: \n79: - Executive summary.\n80: - Planning trigger.\n81: - Active finding registry.\n82: - Remediation workstreams.\n83: - Spec seed.\n84: - Plan seed.\n85: - Traceability status.\n86: - Deferred items.\n87: - Audit appendix.\n88: - Optional Resource Map Coverage Gate section when a map existed at init.\n89: \n90: ---\n91: \n92: ## 6. RELATED RESOURCES\n93: \n94: - `references/state/state_format.md` for schemas.\n95: - `references/state/state_reducer_registry.md` for reducer ownership.\n96: - `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md` for STOP fields shown in dashboard/report.\n\n(End of file - total 96 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Deep Review State Outputs\"\ndescription: \"Focused reference for deep-review packet files, markdown outputs, reducer-owned views, and synthesis artifacts.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review state outputs\"\n  - \"review packet outputs\"\n  - \"review dashboard output\"\n  - \"review report output\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\n---\n\n# Deep Review State Outputs\n\nThis reference explains the files operators read during and after a review loop. Use `references/state/state_format.md` for schemas and field-level contracts.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_outputs.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"Deep Review State Outputs\"\ndescription: \"Focused reference for deep-review packet files, markdown outputs, reducer-owned views, and synthesis artifacts.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review state outputs\"\n  - \"review packet outputs\"\n  - \"review dashboard output\"\n  - \"review report output\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\n---\n\n# Deep Review State Outputs\n\nThis reference explains the files operators read during and after a review loop. Use `references/state/state_format.md` for schemas and field-level contracts.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nDeep-review outputs are audit artifacts. Iteration agents write evidence, the reducer writes derived state, and synthesis writes the release-readiness report.\n\n---\n\n## 2. PACKET FILES\n\n| File | Owner | Mutability | Purpose |\n|------|-------|------------|---------|\n| `deep-review-config.json` | Workflow | Immutable after init | Run parameters, lineage, threshold settings |\n| `deep-review-state.jsonl` | Workflow and iteration contract | Append-only | Config, iteration, blocked-stop, pause, synthesis events |\n| `deep-review-findings-registry.json` | Reducer | Regenerated | Active, resolved, repeated, and blocked findings |\n| `deep-review-strategy.md` | Reducer with operator-readable sections | Regenerated/updated | Dimension order, known context, next focus |\n| `deep-review-dashboard.md` | Reducer | Regenerated | Current status, trend, verdict preview |\n| `iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Iteration agent | Write-once | Detailed findings for one pass |\n| `review-report.md` | Synthesis | Final output | Findings-first release-readiness report |\n| `resource-map.md` | Synthesis | Final or disabled | Converged delta evidence map |\n\n---\n\n## 3. ITERATION MARKDOWN\n\nEach iteration file must be non-empty and end with exactly one final verdict line:\n\n```text\nReview verdict: PASS\n```\n\n```text\nReview verdict: CONDITIONAL\n```\n\n```text\nReview verdict: FAIL\n```\n\nThe line maps to the findings in that iteration only. Synthesis computes the final release verdict from the full state.\n\n---\n\n## 4. DASHBOARD\n\nThe dashboard is a status view, not the source of truth. It should display:\n\n- Current iteration and next focus.\n- Active P0/P1/P2 counts.\n- Dimension coverage.\n- Convergence trend.\n- Gate blockers.\n- Provisional verdict.\n\nIf dashboard data disagrees with JSONL, JSONL wins and the reducer must regenerate the dashboard.\n\n---\n\n## 5. FINAL REPORT\n\n`review-report.md` is the handoff artifact. It carries:\n\n- Executive summary.\n- Planning trigger.\n- Active finding registry.\n- Remediation workstreams.\n- Spec seed.\n- Plan seed.\n- Traceability status.\n- Deferred items.\n- Audit appendix.\n- Optional Resource Map Coverage Gate section when a map existed at init.\n\n---\n\n## 6. RELATED RESOURCES\n\n- `references/state/state_format.md` for schemas.\n- `references/state/state_reducer_registry.md` for reducer ownership.\n- `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md` for STOP fields shown in dashboard/report.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":96,"totalLines":96,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_outputs.md","time":{"start":1781761432741,"end":1781761432746}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0e0048a0bc91479b016a33859888e08191974a6fa28f94b54b"}},"id":"prt_ed941dc85001OSpJbCYet5btbL","sessionID":"ses_126bf8e50ffelsFwMkoTKm6SCe","messageID":"msg_ed941ad890011407BiJHC7Vm9R"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781761432754,"sessionID":"ses_126bf8e50ffelsFwMkoTKm6SCe","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_CZt8M5NxbJWMoQMtDRFkpjyE","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/convergence/convergence.md","offset":1,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/convergence/convergence.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Review Convergence\n3: description: Stop condition algorithms, quality guards, and recovery strategies for the autonomous deep review loop.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"review convergence detection\"\n6:   - \"severity weighted stop ratio\"\n7:   - \"legal stop gate bundle\"\n8:   - \"review stuck detection\"\n9:   - \"composite convergence vote\"\n10: importance_tier: important\n11: contextType: implementation\n12: ---\n13: \n14: # Deep Review Convergence\n15: \n16: Stop condition algorithms, quality guards, and stuck recovery for the deep review loop.\n17: \n18: ---\n19: \n20: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n21: \n22: ### Purpose\n23: \n24: Convergence detection determines when the autonomous review loop should stop iterating. After every iteration the orchestrator evaluates three possible outcomes:\n25: \n26: | Outcome | Meaning |\n27: |---------|---------|\n28: | **CONTINUE** | More review work is expected to yield meaningful new findings. Dispatch the next iteration. |\n29: | **STOP** | The review has reached saturation. Proceed to synthesis and verdict. |\n30: | **STUCK_RECOVERY** | No progress detected for consecutive iterations. Attempt a recovery strategy before deciding. |\n31: \n32: Convergence is checked **after** each iteration completes and **before** the next iteration is dispatched. The check consumes the full JSONL state history and the current dimension coverage snapshot.\n33: \n34: Release-readiness states are derived alongside convergence:\n35: - `in-progress` while coverage is incomplete or new P0/P1 findings are still appearing\n36: - `converged` once coverage and stabilization pass without new P0/P1 findings\n37: - `release-blocking` whenever unresolved P0 findings remain active\n38: \n39: When the loop stops and enters synthesis, the workflow emits `{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md` from converged review deltas before compiling `review-report.md`. Operators can disable that write with `--no-resource-map`.\n40: \n41: ### When to Use\n42: \n43: - Evaluating whether the autonomous review loop should stop, continue, or recover.\n44: - Tuning convergence thresholds, stuck-recovery cadence, or stabilization windows.\n45: - Debugging a stuck-recovery escalation or a premature STOP vote.\n46: - Auditing the release-readiness classification logic before shipping.\n47: \n48: ### Key Defaults\n49: \n50: | Setting | Value | Purpose |\n51: |---------|-------|---------|\n52: | `maxIterations` | 7 | Hard ceiling on loop iterations |\n53: | `convergenceThreshold` | 0.10 | General convergence sensitivity |\n54: | `rollingStopThreshold` | 0.08 | Rolling-average STOP vote threshold |\n55: | `noProgressThreshold` | 0.05 | Stuck / no-progress classification threshold |\n56: | `stuckThreshold` | 2 | Consecutive no-progress iterations before recovery |\n57: | `minStabilizationPasses` | 1 | Coverage signal requires at least one stabilization pass |\n58: | `compositeStopScore` | 0.60 | Weighted stop-score needed before guard evaluation |\n59: \n60: ### Threshold Semantics and Sibling Parity\n61: \n62: `convergenceThreshold` (default 0.10) compares new severity-weighted findings (P0=10, P1=5, P2=1) against accumulated findings. Lower values demand more iterations and a higher signal threshold before STOP is legal.\n63: \n64: **Not interchangeable with sibling deep-loop skills:**\n65: \n66: | Skill | Default | Signal |\n67: |---|---|---|\n68: | `deep-review` | 0.10 | severity-weighted P0/P1/P2 ratio |\n69: | `deep-research` | 0.05 | newInfoRatio (negative-knowledge emphasis) |\n70: | `deep-ai-council` (proposed) | 0.20 | adjudicator-verdict stability |\n71: \n72: Carrying threshold expectations across siblings will cause unexpected iteration counts. Tune each skill against its own default and its own signal, not by analogy.\n73: \n74: ### Security-Sensitive Fix Overrides\n75: \n76: > **STATUS: SPEC ONLY (future implementation).** The override matrix below describes the contract that a future release should apply automatically when the review target involves security-sensitive surfaces. As of v1.9.0.0, the runtime does NOT auto-detect security-sensitivity and does NOT apply these overrides. `requiredClosedFindingReplay` and `requiredFixCompletenessGate` exist in no config / yaml / reducer surface (verified by grep). Operators running a security-sensitive review must manually tighten thresholds via `--convergence` + `--max-iterations` and manually maintain the closed-gate replay table. The contract below stands as the target spec for the next implementation pass. (Provenance for this deferred contract is recorded in this skill's changelog.)\n77: \n78: For review reruns after fixes involving security, path disclosure, auth/authz, sandboxing, env precedence, public schemas, persistence, or user-visible error payloads (intended contract, not yet runtime-enforced):\n79: \n80: | Setting | General Default | Security-Sensitive Fix Default |\n81: |---------|-----------------|--------------------------------|\n82: | `minStabilizationPasses` | 1 | 2 |\n83: | `requiredClosedFindingReplay` | false | true for prior P0/P1 and any prior security/path P2 |\n84: | `requiredFixCompletenessGate` | false | true |\n85: \n86: When implemented, STOP must not be legal until the review report contains a closed-gate replay table that marks each prior active or remediated P0/P1 as `PASS`, `FAIL`, or `carried forward`, with file:line or command evidence. Operators today must enforce this rule manually.\n87: \n88: ### Shared Stop Contract\n89: \n90: Every terminal stop and every blocked-stop vote MUST emit the shared stop contract from REQ-001: a named `stopReason` enum plus, when STOP is vetoed, a `blocked_stop` event written to `deep-review-state.jsonl`. There is no nested `legalStop` wrapper on the persisted path. Earlier drafts of this document implied one, and that drift was the source of F009 in the 042 closing audit.\n91: \n92: #### stopReason Enum\n93: \n94: | `stopReason` | Meaning |\n95: |--------------|---------|\n96: | `converged` | All convergence signals met and legal-stop gates passed. |\n97: | `maxIterationsReached` | Iteration limit hit before convergence. |\n98: | `userPaused` | User requested pause via sentinel. |\n99: | `blockedStop` | Convergence math voted stop but legal-stop gates failed. |\n100: | `stuckRecovery` | Stuck detection triggered recovery. |\n101: | `error` | Unrecoverable error during iteration or reducer flow. |\n102: | `manualStop` | Operator explicitly halted outside the pause sentinel path. |\n103: \n104: #### blocked_stop Event (canonical, persisted)\n105: \n106: `step_emit_blocked_stop` in both `deep_review_{auto,confirm}.yaml` appends the following record to `deep-review-state.jsonl` whenever the legal-stop decision tree vetoes STOP. The gate names and their shapes are load-bearing, the reducer reads them verbatim:\n107: \n108: ```json\n109: {\n110:   \"type\": \"event\",\n111:   \"event\": \"blocked_stop\",\n112:   \"mode\": \"review\",\n113:   \"run\": 5,\n114:   \"blockedBy\": [\"dimensionCoverageGate\", \"p0ResolutionGate\"],\n115:   \"gateResults\": {\n116:     \"convergenceGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"score\": 0.72 },\n117:     \"dimensionCoverageGate\": {\n118:       \"pass\": false,\n119:       \"covered\": [\"correctness\", \"security\", \"traceability\"],\n120:       \"missing\": [\"maintainability\"]\n121:     },\n122:     \"p0ResolutionGate\": { \"pass\": false, \"activeP0\": 1 },\n123:     \"evidenceDensityGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"avgEvidencePerFinding\": 1.6 },\n124:     \"hotspotSaturationGate\": { \"pass\": true },\n125:     \"claimAdjudicationGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"activeP0P1\": 2 },\n126:     \"fixCompletenessReplayGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"securitySensitive\": false, \"requiredRows\": 0, \"passingRows\": 0 },\n127:     \"candidateCoverageGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"searchDebt\": [], \"missing\": [] },\n128:     \"graphlessFallbackGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"mode\": \"graph_available\", \"missing\": [], \"unavailabilityReason\": \"\" }\n129:   },\n130:   \"graphBlockerDetail\": [],\n131:   \"recoveryStrategy\": \"Dispatch the next iteration at the maintainability dimension and re-check after resolving the remaining P0.\",\n132:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-03-24T15:02:00Z\",\n133:   \"sessionId\": \"rvw-2026-03-24T10-00-00Z\",\n134:   \"generation\": 1\n135: }\n136: ```\n137: \n138: - `blockedBy`: array of gate names that failed (string[], never structured objects). Empty when STOP is legal, in which case no `blocked_stop` event is emitted.\n139: - `gateResults`: named sub-records keyed by `convergenceGate`, `dimensionCoverageGate`, `p0ResolutionGate`, `evidenceDensityGate`, `hotspotSaturationGate`, `claimAdjudicationGate`, `fixCompletenessReplayGate`, `candidateCoverageGate`, and `graphlessFallbackGate`. This is the full 9-gate set emitted by `step_emit_blocked_stop` in both `deep_review_{auto,confirm}.yaml`. Each sub-record has a `pass` boolean plus gate-specific fields (score, covered/missing, activeP0, avgEvidencePerFinding, activeP0P1, securitySensitive, requiredRows, passingRows, searchDebt, mode, unavailabilityReason). The reducer reads these verbatim and does not coerce shapes. `candidateCoverageGate` and `graphlessFallbackGate` are v2-rollout gates, they pass trivially when the review-depth-v2 search path is inactive (no search debt, graph available).\n140: - `graphBlockerDetail`: array of structured graph blockers copied from the latest graph convergence decision. Empty when graph convergence did not veto STOP.\n141: - `recoveryStrategy`: human-readable one-liner describing what the next iteration should do before another stop attempt.\n142: - When the graph convergence verdict is `STOP_BLOCKED`, fold the graph blocker gate name into `blockedBy` and preserve the structured blocker objects under `graphBlockerDetail`.\n143: \n144: ### Decision Priority\n145: \n146: Checks are evaluated in this order (first match wins):\n147: \n148: 1. **Max iterations** -- hard cap, always checked first.\n149: 2. **All dimensions covered + clean** -- all 4 dimensions covered, no active P0/P1, stabilization passed, gates passed.\n150: 3. **Stuck detection** -- 2+ consecutive no-progress iterations.\n151: 4. **Composite convergence** -- 3-signal weighted vote with threshold 0.60.\n152: 5. **Legal-stop gate bundle** -- review-specific stop gates. If a stop vote fails any gate, persist `stopReason=blockedStop` and continue.\n153: 6. **Default CONTINUE** -- none of the above triggered.\n154: \n155: ---\n156: \n157: ## 2. HARD STOPS\n158: \n159: Hard stops are evaluated first and override all other signals.\n160: \n161: ### Max Iterations Reached\n162: \n163: ```\n164: if len(iterations) >= config.maxIterations:       // default 7\n165:   return { action: \"STOP\", stopReason: \"maxIterationsReached\" }\n166: ```\n167: \n168: The loop stops unconditionally. Synthesis runs with whatever findings exist.\n169: \n170: ### All Dimensions Covered with Stabilization\n171: \n172: ```\n173: if coverage.dimensionCoverage == 1.0 and activeP0 == 0 and activeP1 == 0:\n174:   if stabilizationPasses >= config.coverageAge.minStabilizationPasses:\n175:     if buildReviewLegalStop(state, config, coverage).passed:\n176:       return { action: \"STOP\", stopReason: \"converged\" }\n177: ```\n178: \n179: Triggers when all 4 dimensions (correctness, security, traceability, maintainability) are covered, no active P0/P1 remains, at least 1 stabilization pass has occurred, and the 5-gate legal-stop bundle passes. If gates fail, the loop records `stopReason=blockedStop` and continues despite full coverage.\n180: \n181: ---\n182: \n183: ## 3. STUCK DETECTION\n184: \n185: Identifies when the review loop makes no meaningful progress across consecutive iterations.\n186: \n187: ```\n188: function countConsecutiveStuck_review(evidenceIterations, noProgressThreshold):\n189:   count = 0\n190:   for i in reversed(evidenceIterations):\n191:     if i.status == \"thought\":   continue    // invisible to stuck counter\n192:     if i.status == \"insight\":   break       // resets stuck counter (genuine progress)\n193:     if i.newFindingsRatio < noProgressThreshold or i.status == \"stuck\":\n194:       count += 1\n195:     else:\n196:       break\n197:   return count\n198: ```\n199: \n200: **Threshold:** `stuckThreshold = 2` consecutive no-progress iterations (using `noProgressThreshold = 0.05`).\n201: \n202: **Status exclusions:**\n203: - `insight`: Resets stuck counter -- a conceptual breakthrough counts as progress even with a low ratio.\n204: - `thought`: Skipped entirely -- analytical iterations produce no evidence to measure.\n205: \n206: When `stuckCount >= stuckThreshold`, the orchestrator invokes the recovery protocol (Section 8) before deciding whether to continue or stop.\n207: \n208: The recovery entry uses `stopReason=stuckRecovery` while the loop is in recovery. If recovery later terminates the run, the terminal record keeps the same shared enum value instead of minting a review-only label.\n209: \n210: ---\n211: \n212: ## 4. COMPOSITE CONVERGENCE\n213: \n214: Three independent signals each cast a stop/continue vote. Stop when the weighted stop-score meets or exceeds the consensus threshold. The signal set below matches the authoritative 3-signal vote in `deep_review_{auto,confirm}.yaml` `step_check_convergence` and the quick-reference convergence table, the 3rd signal is **dimension coverage**, not a standalone novelty ratio.\n215: \n216: | Signal | Weight | Min Iterations | Measures |\n217: |--------|--------|---------------|----------|\n218: | Rolling Average | 0.30 | 2 | Recent severity-weighted finding yield |\n219: | MAD Noise Floor | 0.25 | 3 | Signal vs noise in newFindingsRatio |\n220: | Dimension Coverage | 0.45 | 1 | Configured review dimensions fully covered AND required traceability protocols covered AND `coverage_age >= minStabilizationPasses` |\n221: \n222: ### Signal 1: Rolling Average (weight 0.30)\n223: \n224: Averages the last 2 severity-weighted `newFindingsRatio` values from evidence-bearing iterations (excludes `thought` status). Votes STOP when the average drops below `rollingStopThreshold` (0.08).\n225: \n226: ```\n227: if len(evidenceIterations) >= 2:\n228:   recent = evidenceIterations[-2:]\n229:   avgRatio = mean(i.newFindingsRatio for i in recent)\n230:   rollingStop = avgRatio < 0.08\n231: ```\n232: \n233: ### Signal 2: MAD Noise Floor (weight 0.25)\n234: \n235: Robust statistical test using Median Absolute Deviation. Votes STOP when the latest ratio is at or below the computed noise floor.\n236: \n237: ```\n238: if len(evidenceIterations) >= 3:\n239:   allRatios = [i.newFindingsRatio for i in evidenceIterations]\n240:   med = median(allRatios)\n241:   mad = median([abs(r - med) for r in allRatios])\n242:   noiseFloor = mad * 1.4826     // normal distribution estimator\n243:   madStop = evidenceIterations[-1].newFindingsRatio <= noiseFloor\n244: ```\n245: \n246: ### Signal 3: Dimension Coverage (weight 0.45)\n247: \n248: Highest-weight signal. Votes STOP once every configured review dimension AND every required traceability protocol has been covered by at least one iteration, and the coverage set has been stable for at least `minStabilizationPasses` iterations (default 1). This is the signal the YAML workflow evaluates.\n249: \n250: ```\n251: dimensionStop =\n252:   dimensions_covered_count == configured_dimensions_count\n253:   AND required_traceability_protocols_covered\n254:   AND coverage_age >= config.minStabilizationPasses\n255: ```\n256: \n257: The latest severity-weighted newFindingsRatio is still tracked (the dashboard and registry surface it as `newFindingsRatio`), but it does NOT cast an independent stop vote, it feeds the rolling average and MAD noise-floor signals only.\n258: \n259: ### Weighted Vote\n260: \n\n(Showing lines 1-260 of 584. Use offset=261 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Convergence\ndescription: Stop condition algorithms, quality guards, and recovery strategies for the autonomous deep review loop.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"review convergence detection\"\n  - \"severity weighted stop ratio\"\n  - \"legal stop gate bundle\"\n  - \"review stuck detection\"\n  - \"composite convergence vote\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\n---\n\n# Deep Review Convergence\n\nStop condition algorithms, quality guards, and stuck recovery for the deep review loop.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/convergence/convergence.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Convergence\ndescription: Stop condition algorithms, quality guards, and recovery strategies for the autonomous deep review loop.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"review convergence detection\"\n  - \"severity weighted stop ratio\"\n  - \"legal stop gate bundle\"\n  - \"review stuck detection\"\n  - \"composite convergence vote\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\n---\n\n# Deep Review Convergence\n\nStop condition algorithms, quality guards, and stuck recovery for the deep review loop.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nConvergence detection determines when the autonomous review loop should stop iterating. After every iteration the orchestrator evaluates three possible outcomes:\n\n| Outcome | Meaning |\n|---------|---------|\n| **CONTINUE** | More review work is expected to yield meaningful new findings. Dispatch the next iteration. |\n| **STOP** | The review has reached saturation. Proceed to synthesis and verdict. |\n| **STUCK_RECOVERY** | No progress detected for consecutive iterations. Attempt a recovery strategy before deciding. |\n\nConvergence is checked **after** each iteration completes and **before** the next iteration is dispatched. The check consumes the full JSONL state history and the current dimension coverage snapshot.\n\nRelease-readiness states are derived alongside convergence:\n- `in-progress` while coverage is incomplete or new P0/P1 findings are still appearing\n- `converged` once coverage and stabilization pass without new P0/P1 findings\n- `release-blocking` whenever unresolved P0 findings remain active\n\nWhen the loop stops and enters synthesis, the workflow emits `{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md` from converged review deltas before compiling `review-report.md`. Operators can disable that write with `--no-resource-map`.\n\n### When to Use\n\n- Evaluating whether the autonomous review loop should stop, continue, or recover.\n- Tuning convergence thresholds, stuck-recovery cadence, or stabilization windows.\n- Debugging a stuck-recovery escalation or a premature STOP vote.\n- Auditing the release-readiness classification logic before shipping.\n\n### Key Defaults\n\n| Setting | Value | Purpose |\n|---------|-------|---------|\n| `maxIterations` | 7 | Hard ceiling on loop iterations |\n| `convergenceThreshold` | 0.10 | General convergence sensitivity |\n| `rollingStopThreshold` | 0.08 | Rolling-average STOP vote threshold |\n| `noProgressThreshold` | 0.05 | Stuck / no-progress classification threshold |\n| `stuckThreshold` | 2 | Consecutive no-progress iterations before recovery |\n| `minStabilizationPasses` | 1 | Coverage signal requires at least one stabilization pass |\n| `compositeStopScore` | 0.60 | Weighted stop-score needed before guard evaluation |\n\n### Threshold Semantics and Sibling Parity\n\n`convergenceThreshold` (default 0.10) compares new severity-weighted findings (P0=10, P1=5, P2=1) against accumulated findings. Lower values demand more iterations and a higher signal threshold before STOP is legal.\n\n**Not interchangeable with sibling deep-loop skills:**\n\n| Skill | Default | Signal |\n|---|---|---|\n| `deep-review` | 0.10 | severity-weighted P0/P1/P2 ratio |\n| `deep-research` | 0.05 | newInfoRatio (negative-knowledge emphasis) |\n| `deep-ai-council` (proposed) | 0.20 | adjudicator-verdict stability |\n\nCarrying threshold expectations across siblings will cause unexpected iteration counts. Tune each skill against its own default and its own signal, not by analogy.\n\n### Security-Sensitive Fix Overrides\n\n> **STATUS: SPEC ONLY (future implementation).** The override matrix below describes the contract that a future release should apply automatically when the review target involves security-sensitive surfaces. As of v1.9.0.0, the runtime does NOT auto-detect security-sensitivity and does NOT apply these overrides. `requiredClosedFindingReplay` and `requiredFixCompletenessGate` exist in no config / yaml / reducer surface (verified by grep). Operators running a security-sensitive review must manually tighten thresholds via `--convergence` + `--max-iterations` and manually maintain the closed-gate replay table. The contract below stands as the target spec for the next implementation pass. (Provenance for this deferred contract is recorded in this skill's changelog.)\n\nFor review reruns after fixes involving security, path disclosure, auth/authz, sandboxing, env precedence, public schemas, persistence, or user-visible error payloads (intended contract, not yet runtime-enforced):\n\n| Setting | General Default | Security-Sensitive Fix Default |\n|---------|-----------------|--------------------------------|\n| `minStabilizationPasses` | 1 | 2 |\n| `requiredClosedFindingReplay` | false | true for prior P0/P1 and any prior security/path P2 |\n| `requiredFixCompletenessGate` | false | true |\n\nWhen implemented, STOP must not be legal until the review report contains a closed-gate replay table that marks each prior active or remediated P0/P1 as `PASS`, `FAIL`, or `carried forward`, with file:line or command evidence. Operators today must enforce this rule manually.\n\n### Shared Stop Contract\n\nEvery terminal stop and every blocked-stop vote MUST emit the shared stop contract from REQ-001: a named `stopReason` enum plus, when STOP is vetoed, a `blocked_stop` event written to `deep-review-state.jsonl`. There is no nested `legalStop` wrapper on the persisted path. Earlier drafts of this document implied one, and that drift was the source of F009 in the 042 closing audit.\n\n#### stopReason Enum\n\n| `stopReason` | Meaning |\n|--------------|---------|\n| `converged` | All convergence signals met and legal-stop gates passed. |\n| `maxIterationsReached` | Iteration limit hit before convergence. |\n| `userPaused` | User requested pause via sentinel. |\n| `blockedStop` | Convergence math voted stop but legal-stop gates failed. |\n| `stuckRecovery` | Stuck detection triggered recovery. |\n| `error` | Unrecoverable error during iteration or reducer flow. |\n| `manualStop` | Operator explicitly halted outside the pause sentinel path. |\n\n#### blocked_stop Event (canonical, persisted)\n\n`step_emit_blocked_stop` in both `deep_review_{auto,confirm}.yaml` appends the following record to `deep-review-state.jsonl` whenever the legal-stop decision tree vetoes STOP. The gate names and their shapes are load-bearing, the reducer reads them verbatim:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"blocked_stop\",\n  \"mode\": \"review\",\n  \"run\": 5,\n  \"blockedBy\": [\"dimensionCoverageGate\", \"p0ResolutionGate\"],\n  \"gateResults\": {\n    \"convergenceGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"score\": 0.72 },\n    \"dimensionCoverageGate\": {\n      \"pass\": false,\n      \"covered\": [\"correctness\", \"security\", \"traceability\"],\n      \"missing\": [\"maintainability\"]\n    },\n    \"p0ResolutionGate\": { \"pass\": false, \"activeP0\": 1 },\n    \"evidenceDensityGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"avgEvidencePerFinding\": 1.6 },\n    \"hotspotSaturationGate\": { \"pass\": true },\n    \"claimAdjudicationGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"activeP0P1\": 2 },\n    \"fixCompletenessReplayGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"securitySensitive\": false, \"requiredRows\": 0, \"passingRows\": 0 },\n    \"candidateCoverageGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"searchDebt\": [], \"missing\": [] },\n    \"graphlessFallbackGate\": { \"pass\": true, \"mode\": \"graph_available\", \"missing\": [], \"unavailabilityReason\": \"\" }\n  },\n  \"graphBlockerDetail\": [],\n  \"recoveryStrategy\": \"Dispatch the next iteration at the maintainability dimension and re-check after resolving the remaining P0.\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-03-24T15:02:00Z\",\n  \"sessionId\": \"rvw-2026-03-24T10-00-00Z\",\n  \"generation\": 1\n}\n```\n\n- `blockedBy`: array of gate names that failed (string[], never structured objects). Empty when STOP is legal, in which case no `blocked_stop` event is emitted.\n- `gateResults`: named sub-records keyed by `convergenceGate`, `dimensionCoverageGate`, `p0ResolutionGate`, `evidenceDensityGate`, `hotspotSaturationGate`, `claimAdjudicationGate`, `fixCompletenessReplayGate`, `candidateCoverageGate`, and `graphlessFallbackGate`. This is the full 9-gate set emitted by `step_emit_blocked_stop` in both `deep_review_{auto,confirm}.yaml`. Each sub-record has a `pass` boolean plus gate-specific fields (score, covered/missing, activeP0, avgEvidencePerFinding, activeP0P1, securitySensitive, requiredRows, passingRows, searchDebt, mode, unavailabilityReason). The reducer reads these verbatim and does not coerce shapes. `candidateCoverageGate` and `graphlessFallbackGate` are v2-rollout gates, they pass trivially when the review-depth-v2 search path is inactive (no search debt, graph available).\n- `graphBlockerDetail`: array of structured graph blockers copied from the latest graph convergence decision. Empty when graph convergence did not veto STOP.\n- `recoveryStrategy`: human-readable one-liner describing what the next iteration should do before another stop attempt.\n- When the graph convergence verdict is `STOP_BLOCKED`, fold the graph blocker gate name into `blockedBy` and preserve the structured blocker objects under `graphBlockerDetail`.\n\n### Decision Priority\n\nChecks are evaluated in this order (first match wins):\n\n1. **Max iterations** -- hard cap, always checked first.\n2. **All dimensions covered + clean** -- all 4 dimensions covered, no active P0/P1, stabilization passed, gates passed.\n3. **Stuck detection** -- 2+ consecutive no-progress iterations.\n4. **Composite convergence** -- 3-signal weighted vote with threshold 0.60.\n5. **Legal-stop gate bundle** -- review-specific stop gates. If a stop vote fails any gate, persist `stopReason=blockedStop` and continue.\n6. **Default CONTINUE** -- none of the above triggered.\n\n---\n\n## 2. HARD STOPS\n\nHard stops are evaluated first and override all other signals.\n\n### Max Iterations Reached\n\n```\nif len(iterations) >= config.maxIterations:       // default 7\n  return { action: \"STOP\", stopReason: \"maxIterationsReached\" }\n```\n\nThe loop stops unconditionally. Synthesis runs with whatever findings exist.\n\n### All Dimensions Covered with Stabilization\n\n```\nif coverage.dimensionCoverage == 1.0 and activeP0 == 0 and activeP1 == 0:\n  if stabilizationPasses >= config.coverageAge.minStabilizationPasses:\n    if buildReviewLegalStop(state, config, coverage).passed:\n      return { action: \"STOP\", stopReason: \"converged\" }\n```\n\nTriggers when all 4 dimensions (correctness, security, traceability, maintainability) are covered, no active P0/P1 remains, at least 1 stabilization pass has occurred, and the 5-gate legal-stop bundle passes. If gates fail, the loop records `stopReason=blockedStop` and continues despite full coverage.\n\n---\n\n## 3. STUCK DETECTION\n\nIdentifies when the review loop makes no meaningful progress across consecutive iterations.\n\n```\nfunction countConsecutiveStuck_review(evidenceIterations, noProgressThreshold):\n  count = 0\n  for i in reversed(evidenceIterations):\n    if i.status == \"thought\":   continue    // invisible to stuck counter\n    if i.status == \"insight\":   break       // resets stuck counter (genuine progress)\n    if i.newFindingsRatio < noProgressThreshold or i.status == \"stuck\":\n      count += 1\n    else:\n      break\n  return count\n```\n\n**Threshold:** `stuckThreshold = 2` consecutive no-progress iterations (using `noProgressThreshold = 0.05`).\n\n**Status exclusions:**\n- `insight`: Resets stuck counter -- a conceptual breakthrough counts as progress even with a low ratio.\n- `thought`: Skipped entirely -- analytical iterations produce no evidence to measure.\n\nWhen `stuckCount >= stuckThreshold`, the orchestrator invokes the recovery protocol (Section 8) before deciding whether to continue or stop.\n\nThe recovery entry uses `stopReason=stuckRecovery` while the loop is in recovery. If recovery later terminates the run, the terminal record keeps the same shared enum value instead of minting a review-only label.\n\n---\n\n## 4. COMPOSITE CONVERGENCE\n\nThree independent signals each cast a stop/continue vote. Stop when the weighted stop-score meets or exceeds the consensus threshold. The signal set below matches the authoritative 3-signal vote in `deep_review_{auto,confirm}.yaml` `step_check_convergence` and the quick-reference convergence table, the 3rd signal is **dimension coverage**, not a standalone novelty ratio.\n\n| Signal | Weight | Min Iterations | Measures |\n|--------|--------|---------------|----------|\n| Rolling Average | 0.30 | 2 | Recent severity-weighted finding yield |\n| MAD Noise Floor | 0.25 | 3 | Signal vs noise in newFindingsRatio |\n| Dimension Coverage | 0.45 | 1 | Configured review dimensions fully covered AND required traceability protocols covered AND `coverage_age >= minStabilizationPasses` |\n\n### Signal 1: Rolling Average (weight 0.30)\n\nAverages the last 2 severity-weighted `newFindingsRatio` values from evidence-bearing iterations (excludes `thought` status). Votes STOP when the average drops below `rollingStopThreshold` (0.08).\n\n```\nif len(evidenceIterations) >= 2:\n  recent = evidenceIterations[-2:]\n  avgRatio = mean(i.newFindingsRatio for i in recent)\n  rollingStop = avgRatio < 0.08\n```\n\n### Signal 2: MAD Noise Floor (weight 0.25)\n\nRobust statistical test using Median Absolute Deviation. Votes STOP when the latest ratio is at or below the computed noise floor.\n\n```\nif len(evidenceIterations) >= 3:\n  allRatios = [i.newFindingsRatio for i in evidenceIterations]\n  med = median(allRatios)\n  mad = median([abs(r - med) for r in allRatios])\n  noiseFloor = mad * 1.4826     // normal distribution estimator\n  madStop = evidenceIterations[-1].newFindingsRatio <= noiseFloor\n```\n\n### Signal 3: Dimension Coverage (weight 0.45)\n\nHighest-weight signal. Votes STOP once every configured review dimension AND every required traceability protocol has been covered by at least one iteration, and the coverage set has been stable for at least `minStabilizationPasses` iterations (default 1). This is the signal the YAML workflow evaluates.\n\n```\ndimensionStop =\n  dimensions_covered_count == configured_dimensions_count\n  AND required_traceability_protocols_covered\n  AND coverage_age >= config.minStabilizationPasses\n```\n\nThe latest severity-weighted newFindingsRatio is still tracked (the dashboard and registry surface it as `newFindingsRatio`), but it does NOT cast an independent stop vote, it feeds the rolling average and MAD noise-floor signals only.\n\n### Weighted Vote\n","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":260,"totalLines":584,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/convergence/convergence.md","time":{"start":1781761432748,"end":1781761432752}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0e0048a0bc91479b016a33859888ec8191b34864482b29bd35"}},"id":"prt_ed941dcab001NPgq4Sho49CBB6","sessionID":"ses_126bf8e50ffelsFwMkoTKm6SCe","messageID":"msg_ed941ad890011407BiJHC7Vm9R"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781761432754,"sessionID":"ses_126bf8e50ffelsFwMkoTKm6SCe","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_ifw5ARwSjS1xo4j4mLqDCWgq","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_reducer_registry.md","offset":1,"limit":220},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_reducer_registry.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Deep Review State Reducer And Registry\"\n3: description: \"Focused reference for reducer ownership, findings registry semantics, fail-closed behavior, and reconstruction rules.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep review reducer registry\"\n6:   - \"review findings registry\"\n7:   - \"deep review reducer ownership\"\n8:   - \"review state reconstruction\"\n9: importance_tier: important\n10: contextType: implementation\n11: ---\n12: \n13: # Deep Review State Reducer And Registry\n14: \n15: The reducer is the single writer for derived review state. Iteration agents append evidence; the reducer reconciles it into registry, dashboard, and strategy views.\n16: \n17: ---\n18: \n19: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n20: \n21: The reducer turns append-only review evidence into the current findings registry, dashboard, and strategy state. It is the authority for derived outputs, not a second source of truth.\n22: \n23: ---\n24: \n25: ## 2. OWNERSHIP\n26: \n27: | Surface | Writer | Rule |\n28: |---------|--------|------|\n29: | JSONL state | Workflow plus validated iteration append | Append-only |\n30: | Findings registry | `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` | Regenerate from JSONL |\n31: | Dashboard | `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` | Regenerate from registry and latest events |\n32: | Strategy machine sections | `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` | Update from coverage and findings |\n33: | Iteration markdown | Review iteration agent | Write-once |\n34: | Review report | Synthesis | Final handoff |\n35: \n36: No agent should hand-edit reducer-owned derived state as the authoritative fix. Repair JSONL or rerun the reducer.\n37: \n38: ---\n39: \n40: ## 3. FINDINGS REGISTRY\n41: \n42: The registry groups findings into:\n43: \n44: - Active findings.\n45: - Resolved findings.\n46: - Repeated findings.\n47: - Blocked or disputed findings.\n48: - Claim-adjudicated severity changes.\n49: \n50: Each active finding needs severity, category, file:line evidence, finding class, content hash, first-seen iteration, and latest-seen iteration.\n51: \n52: ---\n53: \n54: ## 4. FAIL-CLOSED BEHAVIOR\n55: \n56: The reducer must refuse to publish derived state when JSONL is corrupt in strict mode. That protects dashboards and verdict previews from silently losing findings.\n57: \n58: Recovery order:\n59: \n60: 1. Identify the malformed JSONL line.\n61: 2. Repair or remove only the invalid appended record with an audit note.\n62: 3. Re-run the reducer.\n63: 4. Confirm registry and dashboard regenerate from the repaired log.\n64: \n65: ---\n66: \n67: ## 5. RECONSTRUCTION\n68: \n69: When derived files are missing but JSONL and iteration markdown exist:\n70: \n71: 1. Rebuild the registry from JSONL finding details.\n72: 2. Rebuild dashboard metrics from registry and latest convergence events.\n73: 3. Rebuild strategy from completed dimensions and active findings.\n74: 4. Re-run synthesis only after reducer outputs are consistent.\n75: \n76: If JSONL is incomplete but iteration files exist, recovery is manual and must be recorded before release readiness is claimed.\n77: \n78: ---\n79: \n80: ## 6. FINDING DEDUPLICATION\n81: \n82: The reducer deduplicates findings at synthesis time using a two-tier match.\n83: \n84: ### Two-Tier Match\n85: \n86: 1. **PRIMARY: content_hash** = `sha256(file_path + line_range + finding_type + normalized_description_80chars)`\n87:    - `file_path`: repo-relative path of the finding\n88:    - `line_range`: e.g., `\"42\"` or `\"42-56\"`\n89:    - `finding_type`: one of `security`, `correctness`, `performance`, `maintainability`, `test_quality`, `contract_safety`, `removal`\n90:    - `normalized_description_80chars`: first 80 characters of the description, whitespace-collapsed and lowercased\n91: 2. **FALLBACK (legacy records): file:line + normalized_title** - applied when one or both records lack a `content_hash`, preserving existing behavior unchanged.\n92: \n93: ### Synthesis Behavior\n94: \n95: When the same `content_hash` appears across iterations from different dimensions, synthesis collapses them to ONE entry with `dimensions: [<all dimensions that emitted it>]` rather than emitting multiple records. Records without `content_hash` fall back to `file:line + normalized_title`; no migration is required for existing JSONL state.\n96: \n97: ### Emission Requirement\n98: \n99: Every finding emitted into the JSONL delta (`findingDetails[]`) MUST include a `content_hash` field computed per the two-tier match. `reduce-state.cjs` reads this field for synthesis dedup.\n100: \n101: ---\n102: \n103: ## 7. RELATED RESOURCES\n104: \n105: - `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` is the reducer implementation.\n106: - `references/state/state_format.md` defines state records.\n107: - `references/state/state_outputs.md` defines operator-visible outputs.\n108: - `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md` defines STOP fields reducer views display.\n\n(End of file - total 108 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Deep Review State Reducer And Registry\"\ndescription: \"Focused reference for reducer ownership, findings registry semantics, fail-closed behavior, and reconstruction rules.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review reducer registry\"\n  - \"review findings registry\"\n  - \"deep review reducer ownership\"\n  - \"review state reconstruction\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\n---\n\n# Deep Review State Reducer And Registry\n\nThe reducer is the single writer for derived review state. Iteration agents append evidence; the reducer reconciles it into registry, dashboard, and strategy views.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_reducer_registry.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"Deep Review State Reducer And Registry\"\ndescription: \"Focused reference for reducer ownership, findings registry semantics, fail-closed behavior, and reconstruction rules.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review reducer registry\"\n  - \"review findings registry\"\n  - \"deep review reducer ownership\"\n  - \"review state reconstruction\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\n---\n\n# Deep Review State Reducer And Registry\n\nThe reducer is the single writer for derived review state. Iteration agents append evidence; the reducer reconciles it into registry, dashboard, and strategy views.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nThe reducer turns append-only review evidence into the current findings registry, dashboard, and strategy state. It is the authority for derived outputs, not a second source of truth.\n\n---\n\n## 2. OWNERSHIP\n\n| Surface | Writer | Rule |\n|---------|--------|------|\n| JSONL state | Workflow plus validated iteration append | Append-only |\n| Findings registry | `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` | Regenerate from JSONL |\n| Dashboard | `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` | Regenerate from registry and latest events |\n| Strategy machine sections | `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` | Update from coverage and findings |\n| Iteration markdown | Review iteration agent | Write-once |\n| Review report | Synthesis | Final handoff |\n\nNo agent should hand-edit reducer-owned derived state as the authoritative fix. Repair JSONL or rerun the reducer.\n\n---\n\n## 3. FINDINGS REGISTRY\n\nThe registry groups findings into:\n\n- Active findings.\n- Resolved findings.\n- Repeated findings.\n- Blocked or disputed findings.\n- Claim-adjudicated severity changes.\n\nEach active finding needs severity, category, file:line evidence, finding class, content hash, first-seen iteration, and latest-seen iteration.\n\n---\n\n## 4. FAIL-CLOSED BEHAVIOR\n\nThe reducer must refuse to publish derived state when JSONL is corrupt in strict mode. That protects dashboards and verdict previews from silently losing findings.\n\nRecovery order:\n\n1. Identify the malformed JSONL line.\n2. Repair or remove only the invalid appended record with an audit note.\n3. Re-run the reducer.\n4. Confirm registry and dashboard regenerate from the repaired log.\n\n---\n\n## 5. RECONSTRUCTION\n\nWhen derived files are missing but JSONL and iteration markdown exist:\n\n1. Rebuild the registry from JSONL finding details.\n2. Rebuild dashboard metrics from registry and latest convergence events.\n3. Rebuild strategy from completed dimensions and active findings.\n4. Re-run synthesis only after reducer outputs are consistent.\n\nIf JSONL is incomplete but iteration files exist, recovery is manual and must be recorded before release readiness is claimed.\n\n---\n\n## 6. FINDING DEDUPLICATION\n\nThe reducer deduplicates findings at synthesis time using a two-tier match.\n\n### Two-Tier Match\n\n1. **PRIMARY: content_hash** = `sha256(file_path + line_range + finding_type + normalized_description_80chars)`\n   - `file_path`: repo-relative path of the finding\n   - `line_range`: e.g., `\"42\"` or `\"42-56\"`\n   - `finding_type`: one of `security`, `correctness`, `performance`, `maintainability`, `test_quality`, `contract_safety`, `removal`\n   - `normalized_description_80chars`: first 80 characters of the description, whitespace-collapsed and lowercased\n2. **FALLBACK (legacy records): file:line + normalized_title** - applied when one or both records lack a `content_hash`, preserving existing behavior unchanged.\n\n### Synthesis Behavior\n\nWhen the same `content_hash` appears across iterations from different dimensions, synthesis collapses them to ONE entry with `dimensions: [<all dimensions that emitted it>]` rather than emitting multiple records. Records without `content_hash` fall back to `file:line + normalized_title`; no migration is required for existing JSONL state.\n\n### Emission Requirement\n\nEvery finding emitted into the JSONL delta (`findingDetails[]`) MUST include a `content_hash` field computed per the two-tier match. `reduce-state.cjs` reads this field for synthesis dedup.\n\n---\n\n## 7. RELATED RESOURCES\n\n- `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` is the reducer implementation.\n- `references/state/state_format.md` defines state records.\n- `references/state/state_outputs.md` defines operator-visible outputs.\n- `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md` defines STOP fields reducer views display.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":108,"totalLines":108,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/references/state/state_reducer_registry.md","time":{"start":1781761432750,"end":1781761432753}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0e0048a0bc91479b016a33859888fc8191afcc5a09394dbcf2"}},"id":"prt_ed941dcad001JsnZVe5ykbmOAp","sessionID":"ses_126bf8e50ffelsFwMkoTKm6SCe","messageID":"msg_ed941ad890011407BiJHC7Vm9R"}}
